title: beef in beer
directions: Fry bacon pieces in large pan.
Leave bacon in pan.
Add beef and brown in bacon drippings.
Add onion and leeks and lightly brown.
Stir in a little flour.
Add beer, stirring constantly. If necessary, add water to cover meat.
Season with salt, pepper and mixed salad herbs.
Add carrots and bring to a boil.
Simmer gently for 2 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
(Can be cooked in a moderate oven, 350°, in covered dish for 2 1/2 hours.)
Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley (optional).

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and salt in a bowl, then add in this order: beaten eggs, potato water and yeast water.
Mix.
Cream the shortening and flour; add.
Mix to form a soft dough.
Let rise until double, punch down and form rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: easy and quick zucchini rice dish
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add garlic powder and salt.
Stir until coated. Add rice (uncooked).
Stir until coated.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Add hot water (1 1/2 cups).
Turn burner down to simmer. Cover.
Steam until water is absorbed (about 5 minutes).
Fluff with fork and serve hot.

title: scalloped irish potatoes and onions
directions: Into a baking dish, put a layer of thin sliced potatoes, salt, pepper and dots of butter.
Add a layer of thin sliced onions. Cover these with dots of butter, salt and pepper.
Repeat until all potatoes and onions are used.
Pour enough milk over potatoes and onions to cover them.
Cook in a moderate oven until potatoes are well browned.
These proportions may be varied according to the size of the casserole.
Serves 6.

title: an appetizer of fruits and cottage cheese
directions: Combine
the
salad
dressing
and
the cottage cheese; blend well.
On
lettuce, arrange the sliced fruits around the blended cottage cheese
mixture.
Chill
and serve as an appetizer before meal or at a party.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brunch bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with slices of white bread.
Top with ham and cheese.
Cover with wheat bread.
Mix together in a bowl the milk, eggs, dry mustard and salt.
Pour over bread.
Mix melted butter and cornflakes together and sprinkle on top of bread.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 5 minutes in 325° oven.
Let set for 5 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: In skillet brown beef,
onion, and pepper; drain.
In a saucepan cook macaroni
according
to
directions.
After beef has browned, add tomato paste, water, cheese, butter and chili seasoning; let simmer
until
macaroni
is
done cooking.
Mix meat mixture and
macaroni together well.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: andrea's macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Grate cheese. In microwave bowl, mix milk, flour, butter, mustard and salt. Microwave 1 minute.
Stir and microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Put macaroni into greased casserole dish.
Pour sauce over top.
Cut bread into cubes and put on top.
Add cheese and bake 45 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; stir until well blended.
Place 1 lettuce leaf on each flour tortilla.
Spread with 1/4 cup chicken mixture down center of each leaf.
Fold lettuce leaf over filling.
Roll up tortillas, enclosing filling.
Wrap each filled tortilla, seam side down, in plastic wrap.
Makes 4.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Stir-fry onion and bell pepper in margarine or shortening. Then add soups, tomatoes, garlic salt and chili powder.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and seasonings and stir until smooth.
Slowly add the milk, stirring constantly.
When it thickens, melt the grated cheese in the sauce.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Slice onions into frying pan and cook slowly in shortening. Saute meat with onions.
Arrange meat and corn in casserole in 4 layers.
Season with salt and pepper and cover with tomato soup. Put mashed potatoes on top.
Brush top with beaten egg yolk and bake in a 450° oven until potatoes brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all.
Put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up one fryer and dip in melted butter.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place chicken on top of mix and bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: hot wassail
directions: Stud lemon or orange with cloves.
Mix other ingredients in a pot.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 30 minutes, covered. Cool slightly.
(I perk it in my coffee pot; a small orange will fit in the top section.)

title: longhorn beef round up
directions: Cook chuck roast in slow cooker. Shred with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and cook down 1 to 2 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in pot of water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Beat 4 or 6 times with mixer to get out strings in potatoes while hot.
Beat eggs well.
Add condensed milk, sugar to taste, butter, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes, until firm and not shaking or test with a knife in middle comes clean.

title: brown and serve sausage crescent rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together as paste.
Spread paste on uncooked crescent rolls.
Add sausage and roll up.
Bake as directed on crescent roll package.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Liquefy all ingredients except salmon for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes; combine with salmon.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until center is firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: taco saladfort collins, colorado
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain, season with the taco seasoning as directed.

title: canned mullet
directions: Clean mullet and debone.
Put in pint jars and sprinkle 1 teaspoon of salt on top of fish.
Seal the jars and place in a pressure cooker.
Get the pressure to ten pounds and cook for 90 minutes.
A good substitute for salmon in any recipe.

title: layered meal
directions: Place meat, onions and bell pepper in skillet.
Brown.
Drain fat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt, chili powder and black pepper.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with sliced potatoes.
Sprinkle rice evenly over potatoes and add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spread meat mixture over rice, then pour tomatoes evenly over meat.
Mix catsup and water.
Pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: microwave vegetable medley
directions: Dice vegetables and combine with butter, salt, pepper and water.
Put in microwave-safe covered dish and cook on High for 20 minutes.
Stir and cook for 15 more minutes.

title: microwave chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt chips in a glass bowl in microwave.
Add peanuts and stir together.
Drop by spoonfuls into small candy paper cups or on wax paper.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix Rice Krispies and peanut butter together.
Form into balls and put on wax paper.
Stick a toothpick into each ball.
Place in refrigerator for one hour.
Melt chocolate chips and wax together. Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper and cool.

title: chicken fried rice(chinese style)
directions: Set wok on high.
Pour 1 tablespoon oil in wok.
Add eggs quickly.
Stir until solid.
Set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon oil and chicken.
Stir quickly until done.
Add all other ingredients, stirring constantly.
Add soy sauce as you are cooking (you can use more soy sauce if desired).
This is done when peas are no longer frozen (15 to 20 minutes).

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Steam broccoli until tender and chop.
Place half-and-half and water in top of double boiler.
Add cheese, salt, and pepper. Heat until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli.
Mix cornstarch and cold water in a small bowl.
Stir into cheese mixture in double boiler and heat over simmering water until soup thickens.
Serves 8.

title: russian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger, onions and garlic in skillet.
Make a gravy of flour, ground chili and water.
Pour this over the cooked meat and add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Very hot.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Place 1/2 cheese on bottom of pie shell. Mix remaining cheese, spinach and chicken, then place in pie shell. Whisk eggs, mayonnaise and milk together, then pour over pie shell. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, apple pie filling, eggs, water and raisins. Blend at low speed.
Mix with electric mixer for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread batter in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping on cake.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is tender and brown. Drain fat. Stir in undrained tomatoes and next 4 ingredients. Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Blend in other ingredients. Pour into 2 bread pans or three 1-pound coffee cans.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour (test with toothpick).

title: german gunk
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk on stove; let cool.
Add whipping cream and mix.
Place layer of graham cracker crumbs in pan, then pour layer of filling.
Repeat layers until finished.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Cut in slices to serve.

title: red potato soup
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and cook for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender. Drain and set aside.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: In a 12 x 18-inch Pyrex dish, layer pineapple, cake mix and cherries in this order.
Melt butter and pour over top and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° until brown, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cut Crab Delight flakes in half.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving. Yields 2 cups.

title: pork chop-stuffing bake
directions: Trim fat from chops.
In skillet, cook trimmings until, about 1 tablespoon fat.
Brown the chops in hot fat; season with salt and pepper.
Remove chops from pan.
Add butter to drippings in skillet.
Add celery and onion, cook until tender.
Remove skillet from heat; add stuffing mix, tossing to coat.
Combine egg and corn; blend with stuffing.
Spoon mixture into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook vegetables in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Sprinkle over stuffing mixture.
Top with browned chops.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle chops with paprika.

title: jessie's sweet pickles
directions: Add 1 cup salt to 1 gallon of vegetables; set for 3 days. Drain and rinse well.
Add 2 tablespoons alum per gallon and cover with water.
Set for 24 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Cover with vinegar and 1 tablespoon turmeric (per gallon) for color.
Set for 10 days.
Drain and add 3 cups of sugar per day for 2 or 3 days according to taste.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix with butter and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour half of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
To the top of the done cake, add chips, nuts and melted caramels.
Pour remaining cake batter over caramels.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together and put in a pie crust. Place in refrigerator to set.
May use fruit cocktail instead of pineapple.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well and chill. Garnish with more eggs, small tomato halves, and/or olives if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: In 2 qt. sauce pan mix butter, brown sugar and corn syrup. Bring to boil. Take off heat. Add baking soda. It will foam.
Pour sauce over corn pops or curls. On cake pan, stir until mixed. Bake in warm oven 250° for 45 minutes.

title: diabetic brownies
directions: Place all ingredients into bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Put into greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip meat in eggs, then flour mixture.
Cook meat in about a cup of hot oil.
When done, put in oven to keep warm.
Melt butter.
Cook pepper and onions until brown.
Add soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, pineapple juice and water with cornstarch.
When thick, add chunk pineapple. Mix with meat and rice.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta (not too soft).
Rinse in cold water.
Cut vegetables.
Mix with pasta.
Add dry seasonings and bottle of Zesty Italian dressing.
Mix together.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese to taste.
Refrigerate.
Better if made the day before.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In large skillet or Wok, stir-fry chicken in oil over medium-high heat until no longer pink, 5-6 min. Remove chicken and keep warm. Stir-fry onions, carrots,green pepper, and mushrooms until crisp and tender, about 5 min.

In a small bowl combine, chicken broth, cornstarch, soy sauce, and ginger. Add to skillet; Cook and stir till thick and bubbly. Return chicken and pea pods to skillet. Cook and stir until heated through. If desired, serve over rice and top with cashews.
Serves 6

title: three ingredient chili
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat 3 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: spinach-cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix together with onion soup mix, sour cream and salt.
Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Top with cheese and stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flour, milk, eggs and sugar.
Melt butter in skillet or griddle.
Pour batter into hot pan or griddle.
Let pancakes cook until holes appear and then flip.
Serve with butter and hot syrup.

title: candy
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients with mixer.
Add next 2 ingredients, blend well.
Grease platter.
Press candy into it and leave it in the refrigerator to cool.

title: sammy's iced potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket until well done. Cool and remove skin. Mash potatoes with a fork well to remove all lumps. Beat eggs and add to potatoes. Add melted butter and beat. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 300° for about 30 to 40 minutes, until firm.

title: broccoli-rice quiche(makes 3 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, combine rice with 1 egg and 1 ounce Cheddar cheese. Press mixture firmly over bottom and sides of an 8-inch pie pan to form a crust; set aside.

title: orange gelatin ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Immediately add sherbet and stir until melted.
Add oranges.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart ring mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on greens.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over top of nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and add cream cheese and powdered sugar. Drop by spoonfuls over top of cake mix.
Do not spread.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and blend all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball and roll in parsley or nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients.
Add lime and garlic and enjoy.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook on cookie sheet at 325° until sizzling stops.
Don't cook until brown.

title: potato cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be stiff.
Let dough chill for 1 hour in "fridge."
Shape dough into marble size balls and place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.
(These really taste like coconut cookies.)

title: lemon cake delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well. Combine the walnuts, sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
In a lightly greased tube pan, spread half of the cake mixture. Sprinkle half of the walnut mixture. Repeat again. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool and serve.

title: jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Store in refrigerator until needed.

title: baby food bars
directions: Mix eggs and oil.
Add sugar, salt, flour, soda, baby food and cinnamon.
Mix together and pour into a greased and floured 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook to a soft ball; boil about 7 to 8 minutes.
Add 1/2 pound raw Spanish peanuts or 1 1/2 cups and the butter.
Cook to a golden brown.
Add soda and vanilla.
Stir about 10 seconds and pour out on a buttered cookie sheet.
Don't spread; let spread by itself.
When good and cold, break into small pieces.
Store in jar and seal.

title: swiss onion soup
directions: Saute onion in butter over very low heat until onion becomes a light golden brown.
Takes nearly an hour.
Stir in soup, 2 soup cans of water, brown sugar, thyme and bay leaf.
Bring mixture to a boil; let simmer 2 or 3 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Make roux with butter and flour; cook until medium brown.
Add milk, 1/4 cup onion, 8 ounces of American cheese, 8 ounces of Cheddar cheese, bouillon, green chilies, cumin and picante sauce. Stir over medium heat until all is melted.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Mix margarine (or shortening), sugars and eggs.

Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt, add to sugar mixture and mix well. Add vanilla, quick oats, Rice Krispies and coconut; mix well. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: naked apple pie
directions: Beat egg in a medium-sized bowl.
Add brown and white sugars and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Sift into egg mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.

title: baked pears in burgundy sauce* * * * *
directions: What could be better on a cold winter day than a bowl of chili?
Eileen is a cousin's wife who came originally from East St.
Louis, Illinois.
I'm sure she found this recipe when she moved to Texas and am I glad she did.
The Burgundy Pears are French and were served at a dinner we attended in Verdun, France. They were served in small glass bowls and looked so pretty.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet cake
directions: Cook raisins and water until dry.
Mix eggs, oil, Sweet 'N Low, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and applesauce.
Add pecans. Fold in raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake on 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick spinach souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Mix and sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown beef; drain. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: hamburger vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo and brown hamburger.
Pour off excessive grease.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5 people.

title: diet soup
directions: Brown beef, drain and rinse.
Empty tomato juice into pot. Fill can with water and add to juice. Simmer bouillon cubes until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients including beef.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and cook on top of stove, stirring constantly.
Before it gets too thick, add the oleo.
Put in baked crust.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chopped chicken with mayonnaise, pineapple and cashews. Serve on crescent rolls.

title: funny cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Pour warm sauce gently over the cake batter.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until cake springs back when touched and crust is brown.
Best when served warm.
For richer cake, use double amount of sauce.

title: c m p cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients well and spread on crust.
Mix vanilla pudding and 1 1/3 cups milk and spread on top of layer 2. Let set 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix chocolate pudding and 1 1/3 cups milk and spread on top of vanilla pudding.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining Cool Whip on top of chocolate pudding. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Refrigerate until set, at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix as given with a large spoon.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 18.

title: grilled corn
directions: Heat coals in grill to medium-hot.
Place grill rack 4-inches above coals.
Peel back husks but leave attached at base.
Remove silk.
Rinse corn, being sure to thoroughly moisten husks.
Brush corn with melted butter.
Pull husks back into place, completely covering kernels.
Grill corn 15 to 18 minutes, turning occasionally.
Serve immediately.

title: candy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, shortening, vanilla and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
(Centers will be soft.) Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.

title: ranch dinner
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet and drain. Add beans and rice. Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve over corn chips.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with fork and wrap in foil.
Put in crock-pot and cook slowly for 8 to 10 hours.
Do not add water.

title: veggie relish
directions: Drain and mix first 8 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Toast the first 4 ingredients on cookie sheet in a 300° oven for 30 minutes or until brown with occasional stirring.
Then add brown sugar to mixture and stir to blend.
Put 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut ice cream in 1-inch slices and place on top of crunchy mixture.
Add rest of mixture on top and freeze. Cut into squares to serve.

title: fruit syrup
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in a saucepan (or in a microwave container).
Cook until it comes to a full boil and all sugar is dissolved.
Put desired fruit in blender.
Add sugar mixture and blend well.
Vanilla is added to banana syrup.
Serve warm.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese with the pudding, then add Cool Whip. Spread on cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over frosting.
Add coconut and crushed nuts, if desired.
I add the cherries for color.
Cool and keep refrigerated.
Eat and enjoy.
Yum yum!

title: microwave sweet potatoes or yams
directions: Cook potatoes 1 inch apart on the oven shelf in a circle. Pierce the skins to allow steam to escape.
Remove potatoes from microwave when fork comes out with a little resistance.
Wrap into foil to keep warm until ready to serve.

title: eclair cake
directions: Spray large casserole dish with Pam.
Line bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Spread with pudding mixture.
Top with graham crackers and frost with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate.

title: lentil barley stew
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Very good; low-fat.

title: caramel cookies
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add pudding mix and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly.
Cool 15 minutes. Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper lined tray.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: easy white frosting
directions: Place egg white and salt in mixing bowl, beat until it stands up in peaks.
Pour in a fine stream over the egg whites the corn syrup, beating constantly about 2 1/2 minutes, or until it holds its shape.
Add vanilla.
Spread on cake.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Lay roast in middle of 5 pieces of heavy-duty foil.
Pour rest of ingredients on top of roast, bring foil up and around and seal completely.
Bake 5 hours at 225°.
When done, you will have a nice roast with gravy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Seems better if frozen awhile.
M-mmm good!

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together thoroughly and bake at 350° for 25 minutes approximately.

title: southwestern cornbread
directions: Beat egg slightly and add milk and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and stir only until moist.
Spread mixture in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: crab dip
directions: Stir lemon juice through crab meat and refrigerate for 30 minutes or more.
Mix cream cheese with remaining ingredients and blend well.
Gently fold in crab meat and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: dawna's black bean soup
directions: *Tie together thyme, basil, parsley and a bay leaf in a net.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut corn from cob, scraping cob to remove pulp.
Combine corn and sugar.
Chill 1 hour.
Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add corn.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in salt and pepper and cream.
Serve warm.

title: stuffed cubanella peppers
directions: Soak bread in water to soften.
Cook and drain sausage.
Add softened bread, minced garlic, cheese and pepper to sausage.
Core out peppers and stuff with mix.
Bake or fry peppers in oil.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add well beaten eggs and bananas and mix well; add lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: You will need a 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Oil the pie plate.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Melt the berries in the jello mixture.
Add the pineapple, lemon juice and nuts.
Put half the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and chill.
Spread the sour cream over this, then add the remaining mixture and chill. Keeps in the refrigerator for days.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add to first mixture. Stir in pineapple and juice.
Fold in bread and a pinch of salt. Bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot. This is excellent with a ham dinner.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and stem mushrooms.
Save stems and set cup aside. Finely chop stems.
Crush crackers.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut bread lengthwise in half. Spread cheese mixture on bread.
Place under broiler until brown and bubbly.
Remove and slice.

title: brandy balls
directions: Blend by hand until pasty.
Pluck off pieces to shape 3/4-inch balls.
Place in container.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken with peanuts and bananas
directions: Bone the cooked chicken and place in a baking dish that will accommodate the chicken in a single layer.	Slice bananas lengthwise and
place
on
the chicken.
Sprinkle with seasonings. Whip the cream
and
mix with chili sauce and pour over chicken and bananas.
Bake	at
for 20 minutes.
Garnish with bacon bits and crushed peanuts.

title: blueberry or grape-nut muffins
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat butter, sugar and egg until light.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Add lightly floured blueberries or same amount of Grape-Nuts. Bake about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice and apricot nectar.
Add ginger ale and add sherbet just before serving.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Just before serving, add 1 to 2 quarts lemon-lime soda or 7-Up.
May also float sherbet in it.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Combine cake mix, peanut butter, eggs and milk; blend at low speed.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and chop onion.
Boil together until tender. Drain off water and mash.
Add cracker crumbs and eggs and mix well.
Add milk and cheese (save enough cheese to sprinkle on top). Add salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together like pie dough, then take out 1 1/2 cups of crumbs.
Put the last 3 ingredients on remaining crumb mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gooey turtle bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter in an ungreased 13 x 9 pan. Stir and press firmly into bottom of pan. Sprinkle with chocolate morsels and pecans. Remove lid from caramel topping. Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 30 seconds. Drizzle over pecans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack. Chill at least 30 minutes. Cut into bars. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: lyrical lime pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, limeade, milk and lemon juice.
Spoon into crusts.
Chill until cold.
May add green food coloring, if desired.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: quick rotel chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil the chicken and debone it.
Save the broth and cook the spaghetti in it.
Mix all the canned ingredients together (works best if you put it in a blender, not all at once).
Mix chicken, spaghetti and soup mixture together in a crock-pot and heat it until
it begins to boil.

title: angel thumbprint cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, egg yolks, salt and vanilla together until fluffy.
Add flour and mix to moderately stiff dough. For each cookie, roll into balls, dip in egg white and roll in chopped nuts.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Using thumb, make a depression in center of each ball. Fill
with jam.
Bake	at
for
20 to 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and strain in a strainer to be sure to remove the stringy parts.
Combine the sugar and Karo together. Combine the margarine and flour together.
Then combine the Karo mixture and the flour mixture together.
Heat only to get hot on stove, being careful not to cook.
Pour the pecans in before you heat the mixture.
After this, pour the mixture in a prepared pastry shell and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with graham crackers.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 1 1/2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Soak bananas in pineapple juice, then add bananas over the mixture.
Add crushed pineapple; cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: cool cookies
directions: Melt 1 cube butter in a saucepan.
Add sugar, milk and cocoa. Boil for for 1 minute.
Add vanilla; remove from heat.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: ham roll
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham slices.
Spread mixture evenly on one side of ham.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick. Cover and chill.
Slice each roll in half and serve with a toothpick.

title: marinated linguini
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate in refrigerator for at least a couple of hours.

title: millie's quick cornbread
directions: Beat shortening, sugar	and
eggs
for	about 1 minute. Add cornmeal, flour and milk and beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: refrigerated potato rolls(yummy and easy)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix together all ingredients and place in oiled bowl. Cover and place in refrigerator. Pinch off dough as needed. Form into shape desired and let rise for 20 minutes at room temperature. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken eden isle
directions: Salt chicken to taste.
Put chicken on a slice of dried beef; wrap with strip of bacon.
Place in casserole or baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Repeat for each piece of chicken breast.
Mix softened cream cheese, sour cream and soup; pour over chicken.
Cover; bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; cook 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges.
Mix jello in hot water.
Add sugar, celery, apples and nuts.
Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator to jell.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Rub into flour and salt.
Put into skillet and brown.
Pour off excess grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: turnovers
directions: Mix first three ingredients as for pie crust.
(May be mixed in food processor.)
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Roll out in confectioners sugar (not flour).
Cut into squares.
Put small amount of Solo filling on each square, fold over and seal.
Bake on foil-lined cookie sheet at 350° about 15 to 18 minutes.
Prick with fork before baking.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen squares.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until translucent.
Add soup and grated Swiss cheese (saving some for topping).
Put in 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbling.

title: stone soup
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add tomato juice and bring to a boil. Add frozen vegetables and cook until tender.
Stir in soups, undiluted, and serve.
(May substitute other vegetables and potatoes.)

title: microwave cherry coconut bars
directions: Place butter in 1 cup glass measure; microwave on High 1 minute.
Set aside.
Break eggs into mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until lemon colored.
Add butter, brown sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into 8-inch round microproof baking dish. Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool completely before cutting into bars or wedges.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to boil, stirring constantly (it will burn on the bottom).
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
You can add cooked broccoli or cooked potatoes just before simmering.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: In the top of a double boiler set over simmering water, combine the bread crumbs, the milk and the cheese and cook the mixture, stirring, until the cheese has melted.
Serve with chips or sliced celery, carrots or chopped broccoli.

title: watermelon preserves
directions: Combine and heat on open fire. Transfer to 350° oven and cook down about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to open fire again. Add juice of lemon and boil down some more. With a bit of water, use 1/4 cup cornstarch to pour into jam.
Stir until thickens.
Add to jars while hot and seal with wax.
Yield varies with size of containers used.
A family favorite!

title: crisco yellow cake(9-inch)
directions: Mix thoroughly 2 minutes at medium speed the first 6 ingredients. Add the eggs, milk and vanilla and beat 2 minutes longer. Pour into greased pans. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: cherry cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water; stir in cherry pie filling and marshmallows.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: squash relish
directions: Cover with cold water. Add 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain off water.
Make syrup.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Simmer salt, pepper, onion, garlic cloves, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and tomato paste for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. While sauce is simmering, boil lasagna noodles, drain and rinse with cold water.
Saute 1 pound of sliced fresh mushrooms in butter and garlic and squeeze with fresh lemon juice.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese.

title: indiana concord grape pie
directions: Remove skin from grapes; set skins aside.
In saucepan, heat pulp of grapes (without any water) just to boiling.
While hot, rub through strainer to remove seeds.
Mix strained pulp with the skins.
Stir together sugar and flour; mix lightly with grape mixture.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save broth and cook spaghetti in it. Before spaghetti is done, chip and chop cheese in or pour in soup.
Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Will make 2 regular casseroles.

title: candied acorn squash rings
directions: Arrange squash in a shallow baking pan; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Combine sugar and butter; spread over squash.
Bake uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes; basting occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coconut pie(very good)
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, milk, flour and coconut. Add vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: over 110-year-old pie crust recipe
directions: Cut lard into flour and salt.
Beat egg until light in color in a 1-cup measuring cup.
Add vinegar and fill cup with cold water.
Add just barely enough liquid to hold dough together, about 4 tablespoons.
Handle dough as little as possible.
Roll out into pastry and proceed as for any pastry.
Makes enough pastry for 2 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press equal portions onto bottoms of 24 lightly greased muffin cups.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon equal amounts of mixture into prepared cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart Pyrex casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler (or any preferred fruit)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. If you are using fresh peaches, peel, pit and slice thin. Put in plastic bowl and pour 1 cup sugar over them. Stir well. Cover tightly and place in fridge for 2 hours. Canned peaches are used as is. Place butter in bottom of rectangular Pyrex baking dish about 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch deep. Put in oven until butter melts. In a bowl, mix the flour, 1 cup sugar and the milk. Beat well with a whisk. Pour mixture over melted butter (don't mix) and spoon peaches over batter mixture. If you are using canned peaches, add only a small amount of juice from the can. If using fresh peaches, use natural juice. Very important: Do not stir peaches into batter. Bake until top becomes golden brown.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat a deep stove-top casserole and add the oil and chicken. Brown the pieces well and then remove to a platter.
Leave the oil in the pan.
Add to the pan the garlic, yellow onion and green pepper.
Saute until the onion is clear and then deglaze the pan with 1/4 cup water.
Return the chicken to the pot and add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, cover the pot and turn to a simmer.
Cook for 25 minutes or until the rice is just tender. This is a basque recipe.
Serves 8. Preparation time:
25 minutes.

title: joyce's pie crust(two crusts)
directions: Mix and roll between 2 sheets of wax paper.

title: salmon fondue
directions: Heat milk in double boiler; add bread, butter and liquid from salmon.
Add beaten egg yolks and salt; cook until thick.
Add cheese.
Cool and add salmon.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in buttered dish.
Place dish in pan of water and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: smashing squash
directions: Slice squash in quarters; cook and drain.
Add carrot and onion to squash. Melt margarine and add to stuffing mix.
Add 3/4 of stuffing to squash; add sour cream and soup.
Mix well.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining buttered stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl until a dough is formed. Pat out on wax paper or floured board until 1/4 thick. Cut in strips 1/2 inch wide and form into sticks 3 to 4 inches long. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° about 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: greek salad
directions: Add other ingredients; mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Make instant pudding according to directions on package; spread on top of sheet cake.
Top with cherries, spreading them over evenly.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cold sweet and sour salmon
directions: Wash and salt the salmon.
Into a pot, place flat on the bottom; pour enough water to cover the slices.
Add the butter, raisins, lemon juice, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Lay the fish in the pot and cook slowly until tender, about 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Remove the fish carefully and place on a rimmed platter.
Let the liquid cook down a little. Beat the egg yolks.
Add a little of the hot liquid to them and slowly add the eggs to the pot.
Cook a minute until smooth.
Pour over the fish.
Serve cold, garnished with parsley and hard-cooked eggs.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle soup with vegetables
directions: Heat all ingredients except for noodles to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes. Skim fat if necessary.
Remove chicken from broth; cool, remove chicken from bones and skin.
Cut chicken into pieces.
Add chicken and noodles to broth.
Heat until hot.

title: green rice and meat
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery, onion, bell pepper and seasonings. Saute until tender.
Add soup, cooked broccoli, rice and Cheez Whiz.
Put in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: In margarine, brown garlic.
Add cream and salt, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Pour this mixture over cooked noodles when cheese is well melted and cream is hot.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put melted oleo in pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together. Pour over oleo.
Pour peaches into pan.
(Do not stir!)
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken and place in casserole.
Mix both soups and put over chicken.
Layer cheese over mixture and then put crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until well done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place 1 layer of margarine, then a layer of broccoli and now a layer of grated cheese.
Pour 1/2 of cream of chicken soup over the layers.
Now repeat this.
Crush the Ritz crackers.
Now sprinkle this as the last layer of the casserole.
Bake in large casserole dish for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cucumbers in sour cream with fresh dill
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Wipe dry and score down the sides.
Slice thin and combine with onion rings, sour cream and cider vinegar, water, salt, white pepper and chopped dill.
Toss lightly.
Turn into serving bowl.
Garnish with sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Serve as a relish.
This is especially delicious with fish.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix well.
Spoon into a greased baking dish.
Top with unbaked pie crust.
Cut slits for the steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix flour and soda together.
Mix egg, buttermilk and vanilla; add to sugar-margarine mixture. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco; gradually add sugar. Add eggs one at a time, blending well. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Begin with flour and end with flour. Add flavorings. Mix well. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 90 minutes. Do not preheat oven. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: jambalaya (shrimp)
directions: In a large heavy pot, add olive oil and cook onions over medium heat until dark brown.
(This will take at least 20 minutes.)
Stir often.
Add celery and bell pepper and cook for a few minutes.
Add shrimp and cook on low heat, about 15 minutes. Add water, salt, black pepper, hot sauce and rice.
Stir once, cover and cook on low heat until rice is fully cooked.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix together butter, flour, sugar, and milk.
Pour into small baking pan.
Pour berries or fruit desired over batter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chili casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix and water.
Press into 9 x 13-inch oven dish. Brown ground beef.
Drain well.
Put beef over stuffing. Sprinkle with onion flakes.
Add corn, then olives.
Spoon chili over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese is bubbly (approximately 20 minutes).

title: spicy shrimp dip
directions: Bring water to a boil; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Drain well.
Rinse with cold water. Chill.
Peel, devein and chop shrimp.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs with fork in a large bowl until frothy.
Add muffin mix, corn, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 13 x 8-inch baking dish.
Saute onions until clear and spread over corn mixture. Spread sour cream over all.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Crumble fine, enough stale biscuits, bread ends and cornmeal muffins for one chicken (1 quart) for turkey (3 quarts).

To this add 1/2 stick margarine or fat from fowl, small finely chopped onion, just enough hot broth to make moist, 2 hard-boiled eggs (chopped fine), 1/4 cup sugar and more salt and pepper, if needed. Mix all together and cook in pan large enough to hold in 400° oven 45 minutes.
Double recipe for turkey.

title: karen's vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for two hours.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Cream shortening or butter; add sugar a little at a time blending well.
Add molasses and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in a thick boiler 5 to 6 minutes. Remove from heat. Add the soda.
Stir well.
Pour on greased foil or dish. When cool, turn over and break into pieces.

title: hot hot mustard dressing
directions: Whisk together vinegar and mustard.
Let stand, covered, unrefrigerated, for 24 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring, until mixture reaches a boil.
Refrigerate.
Use sparingly!

title: chocolate icing (sticky)(an old family recipe)
directions: Combine in saucepan, 2 squares of chocolate, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon butter, 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick. When done add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: lime jello salad
directions: When Jell-O begins to set, whip until frothy.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Fold in the whipping cream and pour in a mold.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Cook butter, sugar and dates until the dates melt.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll in coconut.
Delicious!

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Combine first three ingredients and add hot water.
Cook until thick and bubbly over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Chill.

title: meat 'n tater pie
directions: Allow pie crusts to thaw slightly.
Combine uncooked meat, soup mix, milk, pepper and allspice.
Mix gently.
Lightly pat into pie crust plate.
Top with thawed hash brown potatoes.
Salt and pepper hash brown potatoes to taste.
Add top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cover fluted edges to keep them from browning too much.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until golden brown.
Serve with warm ketchup, if desired.

title: essie's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir well and bake, uncovered at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Apple butter should appear thick and almost transparent.
Stir occasionally.
Spoon into jars, cover and store in refrigerator.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour the first 6 ingredients into greased casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle the American and Parmesan cheeses over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: swordfish marinade
directions: Marinate steaks for 1 hour.
Grill.
Makes enough marinade for 1 swordfish steak.

title: oven stew
directions: Place meat in lightly buttered casserole or small roasting pan.
Add sliced mushrooms, onion and celery; sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Add cream of mushroom soup (undiluted).
Cover tightly with foil 3 to 4 hours at 325°.
Uncover once or twice during cooking period and stir.
You may add a little wine before covering the stew.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon in a wok or large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in wok.
Set bacon aside.
Add vegetables to wok; stir-fry over high heat (350°) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: strawberry-cheese pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Test with knife as for custard pie.
May need a few more minutes, then cool.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease 13 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cookie sheet.
Mix first 2 ingredients until soft dough is formed.
Make into ball on floured surface and knead 20 times.
Place on wax paper and press out a bit.
Place on cookie sheet.
Pinch up tall edge 3/4-inch.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cut-up biscuits with sugar and cinnamon to coat biscuit pieces.
Grease a Bundt pan and layer the biscuit pieces randomly. Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits in Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and remove bread from pan as soon as possible.

title: pineapple orange layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 30 minutes.
Grease and flour three 8 or 9 inch round pans.
Mix cake mix, butter, eggs, oil and oranges with the juice in bowl.
Pour evenly into the pans.
Bake for 30 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes then finish cooling on rack.
Spread filling (recipe to follow) between cake layers and on top of cake.

title: mini pecan muffins
directions: Set oven to 350°. Combine brown sugar, flour and pecans. Set aside. Combine butter and eggs; mix well. Stir into flour mixture just until moistened. Fill greased or paper-lined miniature muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes or until muffins test done. (Mine get done in about 11 to 12 minutes; ovens vary.) Do not overcook. Remove to wire rack to cool. Yields approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together oleo, flour, and powdered sugar. Spread on pizza pan and bake at 350 until lightly brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars and vanilla together until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: diane's chicken spinach salad
directions: Mix
ingredients together through cucumber.
Combine olive oil, white wine vinegar, dried onions, sugar and parsley in separate bowl.
Blend well.
Then toss salad with the dressing.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into a large bowl.
Beat the egg and combine with vinegar and water.
Cut shortening into flour. Sprinkle with egg mixture and mix all together.
Gather the dough into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for about 30 minutes before using.
This dough can be kept in the refrigerator up to 1 week or it may be divided into 4 parts, wrapped separately and frozen.
Makes 4 pie shells or 2 double crusts.

title: no fail divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water together until it forms a hard ball when dropped in water.
Beat egg whites and salt for 3 minutes in large bowl.
Pour syrup slowly into beaten egg whites while beating.
Continue beating until mixture passes the glossy stage.
Add nuts (or fruit) and vanilla, continue beating until mixture forms a peak when beater is raised.
Pour onto buttered platter or drop on waxed paper.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie shell.
Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add Cool Whip. Put in cooked pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: spritz dumplings
directions: Mix all together in glass or metal bowl.
Into boiling broth/water, cut small teaspoon size pieces off side of bowl about 15 at a time.
Cook until they float, about 3 minutes.
You may need to stir lightly with a wooden spoon to loosen from bottom of pan. When cooked, remove with slotted spoon.
Repeat cooking with the rest of the batter until gone.

title: robert's punch
directions: Heat sugar and water to make syrup; add pineapple juice, lemon juice and orange concentrate.
Freeze; take out an hour or so ahead of time before serving.
Add 1 package frozen strawberries, bananas and ginger ale.

title: pork chops risotto
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in a 12-inch skillet in oil; remove and reserve.
Saute rice, onion and green pepper in drippings until rice is golden.
Stir in Hunt's sauce, water and 1/2 teaspoon of salt; bring to a boil.
Arrange chops in rice mixture.
Sprinkle with Italian herb seasoning.
Cover. Simmer 35 to 40 minutes, until tender, adding cheese during the last 5 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 1/3 cup of mixture per 1 cup boiling water.

title: broccoli stuffing casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in buttered baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover for the last 5 minutes cooking time.

title: unsweetened jelly
directions: *Can use any juice such as orange, apple, etc.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in an airtight quart container.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons mixture to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Refrigerate to jell.
Combine cream cheese with sour cream until smooth.
Add sugar.
When gelatin is jelled, spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Best if placed in long, shallow dish.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: irish coffee
directions: Beat whipping cream, powdered sugar and vanilla in a chilled small mixer bowl until stiff; refrigerate.

title: fruit cake bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Add everything else and stir until well mixed.
Do not beat.
Pour into
a
greased
and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated
oven
at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 1 hour in pan on
a wire rack.
Turn right side up on the wire rack and cool again for 1 hour.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix mustard, salt, seed, sugar, oil and vinegar.
Mix well and pour over cabbage and onion.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, mayonnaise, chestnuts, celery, onion, 3/4 cup cheese and soup.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Remove from oven and top with cracker crumbs, butter and remaining cheese, mixed together.
Bake until brown.

title: debra's blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in hot water; cool.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients 10 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in layer pans.

title: lemon zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Flatten biscuits, one at a time, between palms of hands.
Place on baking sheet. Spread tomato sauce over biscuits.
Arrange pepperoni slices on top. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Yields 10 servings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Sprinkle celery and onion salt along with Worcestershire sauce on top.
Crumble parsley over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Add water when chops are about 1/2 done to prevent sticking.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan with cooking spray. Pour pecans
and coconut into pan; set aside.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions, pour over
pecans and coconut.

title: special lemony chicken
directions: In paper or plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; shake to coat.
In large skillet, brown chicken in margarine on both sides until golden brown.
Add ReaLemon juice and mushrooms.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Serve with hot, cooked rice. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: yummy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Cool.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add chocolate mixture, then flour and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan with the bottom only greased.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: giant kellogg's raisin bran cookies
directions: Stir together Raisin Bran, flour and soda. Beat margarine, sugar and brown sugar until fluffy. Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, sugar and salt, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Remove mixture from heat and stir in corn.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of the hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish. Cook 1 hour in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: peach delight
directions: Prepare pudding with milk and sour cream.
Refrigerate.
Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes. Cool.
Spread pudding on cool cake, sliced peaches on pudding and spread Cool Whip on peaches.
Sprinkle pecans on topping.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator several hours.
Serves 12.

title: blintz bubble ring
directions: Cut cream cheese into 20 pieces. Roll into balls. Roll each biscuit to about 3-inch diameter. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Place 1 cheese ball and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture in each biscuit. Pinch dough to seal. Pour melted butter into bottom of 5-cup ring mold. Sprinkle half the nuts and half the remaining cinnamon mixture into mold. Place half the rolls atop mixture, seam side up. Repeat layers. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until browned. Cool 5 minutes in pan. Invert onto serving plate.

title: "sloppy joe" casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as package label directs; drain. Meanwhile, prepare seasoning mix with ground chuck, tomato paste, tomato sauce and 1 1/4 cups water, as package label directs. Preheat oven to 350°. In 2 1/2-quart casserole, layer half the macaroni, half the cottage cheese and half the meat sauce; repeat. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake, uncovered, 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbling. Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp-and-bass spear-it
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Leave tails on.
Roll fish strips. Cut bacon slices in half and wrap half strip around each fillet strip roll.
Melt butter and add lemon juice and minced dill. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
On each of four 12 to 16-inch skewers, spear first shrimp, next mushroom half, then wrapped fish.
Repeat, ending with shrimp.

title: mousse in a minute
directions: Prepare pudding as directed, using milk.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: gram's meat pie
directions: Add potatoes, onion, carrots, celery, salt and pepper to a pot with enough water to cover.
Boil until almost done.
Form ground beef into small meatballs.
Add meatballs and bouillon cube(s) to vegetables.
Cook until done.

title: tuna pate
directions: Mix all ingredients well and decorate with parsley and pimento after molding into desired shape.
Chill.
Serve with crackers. Serves 24.

title: black bean medley
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute until tender.
Add black beans, tomato and rice; stir well. Stir in chopped cilantro and next 3 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat 20 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to a serving bowl.
Garnish with fresh cilantro, if desired.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Do not bake!

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Add in beaten eggs; mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in a shallow pan at 225° to 250°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Spray or grease a 2-quart casserole; layer 1/3 of carrots, onion, cheese and oleo (3 layers each).*
(Last layer has to be oleo.)
Top with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° until the cheese bubbles up through, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and sift first four ingredients.
Combine banana, sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat until light with rotary mixer.
Add sifted ingredients using spoon, mix until well blended.
Add nuts.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Place chicken, water and 1 tablespoon of salt in deep saucepan; cover and simmer about 45 minutes until tender.
Cool.
Remove meat, discarding bones and skin.
Cut chicken in bite size pieces. In a large bowl, combine chicken, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, tomato paste, oregano and basil.
Stir and set aside.
In a lightly greased quiche or deep dish pie pan, layer cottage cheese, then chicken.

title: cookie frosting
directions: Mix all together and frost cut-out sugar cookies.

title: mark's deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Let cool before peeling.
Cut eggs in half and put the yolks in a separate bowl.
Mix mayo, pickles and mustard with yolks.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fill egg halves with mixture; sprinkle paprika on top.
Serve cold.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix
jello
with crushed pineapple.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.	If desired add marshmallows.

title: italian fish roll-ups
directions: Divide fish into 4 portions.
Add beans and onion to boiling water.
Cover and cook for 7 minutes or until beans are tender and crisp.
Drain.
Place 1/2 cup of bean and onion mixture in the middle of each fish portion.
Start with the narrow end of fillet and roll.
Place in baking pan with the end of fillet on bottom. Mix tomato sauce, oregano, basil and garlic powder together.
Pour over fish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until fish flakes easily with fork.
Yields 4 servings.

title: turkey tortilla casserole
directions: Heat 3/4 tsp. oil in a medium non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Add turkey; saute 1 minute. Add 3/4 tsp. oregano, salt, 1/4 tsp. cumin, pepper, two cloves of garlic; saute 1 minute. Add 1/2 cup corn and onions; saute 1 minute. Spoon into a bowl; stir in chopped cilantro.

title: spicy rice a roni
directions: Brown rice package in margarine.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Drain.
Pour tomatoes and green chilies into a 2-cup measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add to meat mixture along with the chili powder and the spice package from the Rice-A-Roni.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring occasionally.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Add oysters to milk.
Mix oleo, cracker crumbs and seasoning. Place 1/2 of the crumb mixture into a baking dish.
Spread oysters over mixture, and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Pour in enough milk to cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fast fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add boiling water and butter. Blend well.
Stir in vanilla.
Frosts tops and sides of two 8-inch or 9-inch layers.

title: alabama tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Place bowl in refrigerator overnight. When ready to bake tea cakes, use a teaspoon and take a small ball of dough out about the size of your thumb.
With your greased hands, roll the dough into a smooth ball and lay on cookie sheet. Press the ball down very flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° until edges are brown.
The chilled dough is easier to work with.
Also keep fork in cup of ice water and it will work better.

title: deviled ham and cream cheese spread
directions: Good for sandwiches or eat on crackers.

title: fudgy oatmeal bars
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: banana-pineapple delight
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter in bowl.
Press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Place in freezer 15 minutes to harden.)
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk until creamy. Spread over graham cracker crust.
Pour drained pineapple over cream cheese mixture.
Place sliced bananas over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy pull apart donuts
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

Mix sugar and cinnamon. Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and drop into melted margarine, rolling to coat. Roll in sugar mixture, randomly twisting and pinching dough in order to incorporate mixture throughout.
Place in rows and bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Loosen edges and immediately invert onto heatproof plate.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix avocados, lemon juice, tomato, pepper, vinegar, mayonnaise and olive oil. Refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Fry and drain bacon; add to other ingredients.
Combine and heat to serving temperature.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Rinse wild rice.
Simmer rice in 1 1/2 cups water and butter until soft.
Set aside.
Chop bacon and onion into small bits. Brown together and set aside.
In large pot, heat cream of potato soup, 1 cup water and milk.
When hot, slowly add slices of cheese.
When cheese is melted, add rice, bacon and onion.
Blend well.
Add milk and simmer about 30 minutes and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and flour gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup.
Beat well.
Add salt and eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Add broken pecans and vanilla.

title: refrigerator dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water.
In another bowl, beat eggs. Add melted butter,
salt, sugar, then add yeast after mixture has cooled to lukewarm.
Beat
in flour.
Store in covered container in refrigerator. When ready to use, make out in desired shapes. Let raise and then bake approximately 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy nut mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In large skillet, melt margarine, stir in sugar, cumin, curry, garlic and cayenne pepper.
In large bowl combine cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Add margarine mixture and toss thoroughly.
Turn into shallow baking pan and bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.
Makes about 8 cups nut mix.

title: stew beef
directions: Mix and cook in a 350° oven about 3 hours or until tender. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: potato-cheese chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, bouillon cubes and onion in water until tender; drain, saving cooking potato water.
Melt in saucepan, the butter.
Sprinkle in flour and let bubble.
On low heat, slowly stir in potato water, milk and pepper.
Cook over moderate heat until bubbling, thick and smooth, stirring constantly, adding more milk if needed.
Turn heat to low and simmer 2 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in potatoes; mash lightly and heat well.

title: thumbprints
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll into one inch balls.	Dip in slightly beaten egg white.	Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place one
inch
apart on ungreased baking sheet and press thumb into center of
each.
Bake
for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool!
Place jelly in thumbprint.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat the eggs at high speed for 5 minutes. Add the sugar.
Add the pumpkin and lemon juice. Blend.
Add the flour, ginger, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.

Pour onto a 15 x 10-inch baking pan, lined with foil. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Turn on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Remove foil and roll towel and cake up. Cool in refrigerator.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Mix together flour, oats and brown sugar in bowl.
Stir in margarine with fork to make crumbly mixture; set aside.
Combine apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish and stir together.
Sprinkle topping over apple mixture.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High or until apple mixture starts to bubble through topping.
Ovens vary in temperature.

title: quiche
directions: For first layer, combine butter, hash brown potatoes, pepper cheese, ham, mushrooms and pizza cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk and salt together; pour over first layer. Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill until firm.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix sour cream, cheeses, chilies, olives, onions, garlic and salt and spread on tortilla shells.
Roll the shells like a jelly roll.

title: pizza crust
directions: Bring milk, sugar, salt and shortening to a boil.
Let cool. Mix together remaining ingredients and add to milk mixture.
Mix well. Cover and let rise.
Roll out onto pan. Top with tomato paste and Pizza Topping.

title: crab shells
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Add the crab meat.
Mix the mayonnaise, lemon juice, egg yolk and parsley.
Fill shell shaped dishes with crab mixture.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of the mixture over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drain olives well and make a ball of the mix around an olive.
Brush with paprika and bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican pin wheels
directions: Mix everything in large bowl, spread on tortillas.
Roll tightly, refrigerate overnight in covered container or glad wrap. Slice the next day.

title: dad's special spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: In large skillet, cook ground meat, onion and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off all fat.
Put all ingredients, except spaghetti noodles, into crock-pot and let simmer all day or may simmer on stove for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix and bake 20 minutes at 350° in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread marshmallow cream over hot cake.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat cider, cloves, allspice, cinnamon and sugar to boil. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain cider mixture.
Put into punch bowl.
Float apple slices in bowl or put oranges in, your choice.
Serves 32, 1/2 each serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and egg until well mixed.
Gradually beat in juice concentrate.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder, oats, nuts and raisins in large bowl.
Stir well.
Mix dry ingredients and creamed mixture together.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes or until lightly browned at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to a boil, margarine, water and cocoa.
Mix well with flour mixture and sour cream and put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add ice cream and stir until dissolved.
Add fruit cocktail.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: famous pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix filling in order given.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix together Oreo cookies and 1/2 cup margarine.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, then freeze.
Add softened ice cream, then freeze.
In saucepan, add evaporated milk, salt, sugar, unsweetened chocolate and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Cook on medium heat until thick, then put in the freezer or refrigerator to cool. When chocolate is cooled, spread it on the ice cream, then freeze 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread it on top of chocolate sauce, then freeze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
Set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend together the eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Pour into a greased pan (thick).
Bake at 350° for one hour in cold oven.

title: diane's curried chicken and broccoli(serves 8)
directions: Place broccoli in casserole and top with pieces of cooked chicken.
Combine undiluted chicken soup with mayonnaise, milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple to warm.
Add Jell-O and mix.
Chill 15 minutes.
Add buttermilk and pecans; chill 15 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and chill until firm.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine hamburger, bread, milk, onion and green pepper.
Shape into meatballs and place in casserole dish.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and disregard tips; pat dry.
Bake on a rack in a roasting pan at 425° for 1 hour, turning 1/2 way through cooking time.
In saucepan, combine hot sauce and butter. Dip wings to coat completely.
Serve with celery and Blue cheese dip.
Makes 12 to 15 wings.

title: churros
directions: In saucepan bring water, sugar and salt to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in flour all at once and beat until smooth. Beat in eggs one at a time until mixture is smooth.
Spoon batter into pastry bag fitted with a large star point.
Pipe 3 inch strips onto waxed paper or floured surface.
Add peel from lemon to a deep fat fryer and heat to 375°.
Fry churros, a few at a time for 3 to 4 minutes until golden brown, turning as necessary. Drain on paper towel.
Cover with sugar.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice with pudding, then add pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and coconut.
Stir in Cool Whip last. Refrigerate until served.

title: applesauce cake(low-fat)
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in about 3/4 of flour mixture, in 3 additions, alternately with applesauce just until blended.
Mix remaining flour mixture, raisins and walnuts; stir. Turn into well greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Good cake and low-fat...enjoy.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend 3 eggs, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese until smooth.
Pour on top of dough in pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.
Cut after the cake has cooled.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix melted butter, cake mix and 1 egg together.
Press in 9 x 13-inch cake pan (ungreased).
Blend the cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar together.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut when cool.
Dee-lish-ous!
Easy and good.

title: mom's beef and vegetable stew
directions: Brown beef cubes in hot oil in a Dutch oven. Remove from pan. Saute onions, green peppers and celery in oil remaining in pan for about 5 minutes or until tender.
Return beef to pan.
Add beef broth, 1/2 cup water, tomato sauce and salad dressing mix.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes, carrots and whole onions. Simmer 1 hour or until meat and vegetables are tender. Remove from heat. Skim off excess fat. Blend flour with 2 tablespoons water.
Stir into beef mixture. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until thickened. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
No salt.
Take meat off bone and set aside. Keep broth for dressing.
Cut up chicken in 1/2-inch pieces. Melt butter.
Pour over dressing; save some dressing for topping.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well and pour into oblong greased cake pan.
Pour the drained peaches on top.
Mix the peach juice, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread mixture over cake and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts and mix well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Shape into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill overnight for well blended flavors. Garnish with cherry and serve.

title: crepes
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry until brown on both sides.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add egg, pineapple, and flavoring.
Sift flour, add soda, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts to flour mixture.
Add dry ingredients to creamed shortening.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by tsp. on well greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven (425 degrees) 10 minutes.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Place the 3 cups of fresh fruit in deep dish crust.
Mix together the sugar and flour; pour over fruit.
Top with butter that is sliced into thin pieces.
Bake at 300° to 325° until the crust turns a golden brown.
The flour, sugar and butter makes the top crust.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix seasoning and bring to boil.
Add onion and cukes and boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Seal in 2 pints or 1 quart.

title: curiosity cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oleo and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Press 1/2 mixture in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over baked crust.
Melt caramels with remaining 1/3 cup of evaporated milk in a double boiler.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips and nuts.
Press remainder of cake over this and bake at 350° for 20 minutes more.
Cool slightly and refrigerate.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with dressing and the 2 tablespoons pineapple juice (taken from reserved juice).
Add reserved cherry juice.
Add drained pineapple, cherries and mini marshmallows. Whip the cream and fold in.
Chill overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape into ball or log.	Roll in chopped walnuts or pecans.

title: chicken noodle dish(to freeze)
