directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and basil.
Stir in chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken.
Mix cottage cheese with egg.
Line a 3-quart casserole with heavy-duty foil.
Lightly grease foil.
Place 1/3 of chicken mixture on bottom of casseroles.
Top with half of noodles, half of cottage cheese mix, half broccoli and Mozzarella cheese and repeat layers.
End with last third of chicken mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Tightly cover with foil and freeze.
To cook, place still frozen in a 350° oven and bake 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: tabouleh
directions: Place burghul in a bowl and cover with cold water.
Leave to soak for 30 minutes.
Drain through a fine sieve, pressing with back of a spoon to extract moisture.
Spread onto a cloth and leave to dry further.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until soft.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine flour with salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken scallopini marsala(makes 4 servings)
directions: Using meat pounder or rolling pin, pound chicken breasts, one at a time, in plastic bag until 1/4-inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: pineapple casserole #2
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour. Crush crackers on top. Melt margarine and pour on crackers. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. The entire recipe has 13 Weight Watcher points.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except berries, until smooth.
Stir in berries. Pour into paper lined muffin tins, about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken diane
directions: In 12-inch nonstick skillet heat half of the margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add chicken and cook, turning frequently, until lightly browned on all sides and when pierced with a fork, juices run clear.
Remove chicken to a plate and keep warm.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Add onions, salt, paprika and diced tomatoes.
Cook pasta well done.
Drain.
Add to hamburger mixture.
Cover; heat for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken stock
directions: In large stockpot, heat boiling chicken over medium-high heat until just boiling. Then reduce to lowest heat and simmer. Add onion (quartered), celery and carrot cut into 2-inch sections. Add salt, pepper and other optional herbs. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Skim froth from surface. Remove chicken. Let cool. Remove meat from bones. Cut into 1-inch pieces and reserve. Return bones and skin to stock and simmer for another 30 minutes. Remove bones, skin and cooked vegetables and reserve chicken stock for other recipes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix preserves, dressing and soup mix together.
Arrange chicken in baking pan, and top with mixture.
Cook in 350° oven for one hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: salsa dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix tomatoes, onions, garlic and onion powder to taste.
Serve immediately or chilled.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in sheet cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: boysenberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin pans.
Into a medium bowl, sift flour and baking powder.
Stir in sugar.
In another bowl, beat together egg, milk, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir just until blended.
Gently stir in boysenberries.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin pans.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until well risen and golden brown.

title: christmas salad
directions: Stir lemon juice into milk.
Mix in cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before serving.
Can be frozen up to two weeks.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water.
Add milk and cheese.
Add chicken bouillon cubes.
Mix half and half and flour.
Add to above mixture.
Heat until hot.
Garnish with croutons.

title: mai tai punch
directions: Combine all and serve frosty cold.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts punch.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Fry as you would pancakes.

title: dot's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make small meatballs; brown in roaster in oven.
Remove excess fat, if any.
Mix remainder of ingredients together; thicken with flour.
Pour over meatballs.
Top with can of chunk pineapple (if desired, add green pepper and mushrooms).
Using casserole dish, heat in oven at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve with king size Fritos.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water; drain and mash.
Add onion, sage, eggs and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle grated cheese and paprika on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: deer steak
directions: Soak steaks in baking soda 15 minutes.
Change water.
Soak in clear water 1/2 hour.
Cut steak into 4 pieces.
Fry in butter. Turn heat to simmer.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.
Keep adding water.
If meat is cut thick, cook 1 hour.
Make sure it is tender.
Before serving, add 1/2 stick butter.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Combine drink mix and sugar according to package directions. Add 2-quarts water.
Prepare orange juice, using package directions.
Combine with cherry drink in punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale.
Add ice or ice ring.

title: chicken spaghetti(serves 15)
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Save the chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth saved and add a couple of cans.	Drain spaghetti and put to the side.
Chop or shred chicken after it cools.
Put stick of butter in frying pan and saute chopped onion, pimentos, mushrooms, water chestnuts, sliced almonds, peas and Ro-Tel.
Cut Velveeta cheese up into small cubes and microwave until all melted, stirring occasionally.
Mix chicken, spaghetti and saute mixture and Velveeta cheese together.
Put in large baking pan and sprinkle with paprika.
Add chicken broth if mixture seems to be dry throughout baking time.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: flour muffins
directions: Cream together the lard, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, well beaten, then dry ingredients, with enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Put in well-greased muffin tins.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: spanish dip
directions: In glass pie plate, line bottom with cream cheese.
Spread the refried beans.
Spread the chili.
Top with cheese.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with corn chips.

title: vegetable soup(low calorie)
directions: Cut up all vegetables and combine with other ingredients. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Makes a large amount, but it can be frozen.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a roux of flour and oil in heavy pot. When browned to dark caramel color, add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic. Cook until soft. Add tomatoes and tomato sauce. Cook 5 minutes. Then add 6 cups water. Add seasonings and sugar. Simmer for 1 hour. Add shrimp. Cook another 15 minutes. Add green onion and parsley. Cook 5 more minutes. Serve over rice. Makes 10 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix dressing in separate bowl.

title: devil's food chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix about half of the cake mix (dry), the margarine, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes (center will be soft).
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix and bring to boil the first 3 ingredients.
Add peanuts and food coloring.
Continue to boil until firm ball is formed. Add butter, salt and vanilla.
Beat until cloudy and creamy and pour into buttered cookie sheet.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in glass baking dish.
Cover with bell pepper slices.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce (your discretion).
Cover with tomato sauce and bake for 45 minutes at 400°, then sprinkle with cheese and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: seafood lasagne by dennis
directions: Heat margarine, in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, until melted.
Add garlic.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese, onions, basil and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.

title: bouillie (vanilla pudding)
directions: Add milk, water and extract in pot and bring to boil. In separate bowl, mix sugar, cornstarch and egg together and stir well. Make sure there are no lumps. A little milk may be added if needed. Add to the boiling milk mixture and cook until desired thickness. Pour over vanilla wafers or cake; bananas may be added if you want.

title: hoosier gooseberry pie
directions: Wash berries and remove stems.
Pat dry.
Place berries, sugar, tapioca, butter, salt and nutmeg in a large saucepan over low heat.
Stir frequently and cook until sugar is melted and berries are soft.
Let cool.
Pour into pie shell and cover with top crust.
Make 5 to 6 slashes in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes longer.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in boiling water until tender; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, eggs, cheese, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and pork, mixing well.
Shape into loaf in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: quick appetizer
directions: Pour into bowl and heat in microwave for 3 to 5 minutes. Filling and delicious.

title: crispy caramel treats
directions: Microwave caramels, margarine and water in 1-quart glass bowl or glass measuring cup on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring every minute.
Pour over cereal; toss until well coated.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit.
Mix the sour cream and sugar together; stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over fruit; stir.
Refrigerate. Keeps for several days.

title: chocolate torte
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix pecans, flour and margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Melt 1 stick oleo and the graham cracker crumbs; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread beaten mixture over crumbs.
Cover with split bananas.
Pour pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip, cherries and nuts (optional).
Chill.

title: macaroni and vegetables
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 6 to 8 minutes; drain. Toss with oil.
Steam vegetables.
Run under cold water and set aside.

title: peanut butter chocolate balls
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar to form balls.
Place balls on a cookie sheet, covered with wax paper. Chill balls for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Put sugar, brown sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil until it forms a ball in cold water.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour in buttered dish and cut when cool.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook squash (cut in 1/2-inch rings) and onion until tender. Drain, saving liquid from squash. Melt butter; add flour gradually until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup reserved liquid from squash.
Cook until thick.
Add salt, 1/2 cup cheese, green peppers and squash.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese, crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Add Italian Dressing and sprinkle Romano Cheese over the top and mix well.

title: pastry shells
directions: Blend ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
When ready to use, roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut circles and form over muffin tins or place in tart pans.
Prick thoroughly with fork to prevent puffing.
Bake at 450° until golden, about 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 15 shells.
Delicious when filled with chicken salad.

title: special baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off grease well.
Mix all other ingredients in 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
This may be doubled to serve as a main dish or used as a side dish.
For larger amounts, increase ingredients and cooking time.

title: baked squash(microwave)
directions: Cut squash into 4 pieces; do not peel and clean seeds out. Mix together butter, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Place on top of squash.
Put a piece of apple on top.
Cook about 5 minutes or until done.

title: rainbow float
directions: Fill a tall glass halfway with red fruit punch.
Scoop 2 medium scoops of lemon sherbet into glass and fill the glass the rest of the way with lemon-lime beverage.
Serve right away. Makes 1 float.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients, put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Melt oleo and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°; top with crushed potato chips last 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grease and flour three 1 pound coffee cans. Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute oil and onion.
Add green and hot peppers.
Cook until tender.
Cook green beans until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa in pan and bring to boil (rolling boil) for 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Combine peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir in well.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: toby's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender;
drain and cut into chunks. (Leave skins
on.) Stir in remaining ingredients, using amount of mayonnaise you desire.
Chill.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a nonstick saucepan, fry rice in about 2 to 3 tablespoons oil.
(Should be just enough so you see the shine on all the rice kernels but not enough that the rice is sitting in a puddle.) Cook over low heat; stir continually until rice becomes light golden brown.
Remove pan from heat.
Let cool a bit.
Add 2 cups of water and put back on low heat.
Add in veggies and onion and a dash of garlic powder (optional).
To this add about 2 or 3 tablespoons of chicken/tomato bouillon flavor and stir.
(If you don't have the tomato/chicken you can get by with just chicken flavor and then add a splash of ketchup.
This is to add flavor but also to give it the pinkish/red color.)

title: dorothea brown's wheat sticks
directions: Mix flour, salt and brown sugar in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add nuts.
Slowly add just enough milk to make it stick together, about 2/3 cup.
Knead in bowl all ingredients about 1 minute.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in strips about 1/2 x 4-inches.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes on greased sheets.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops, then place the pork chops in a large rectangular casserole dish.
Season chops with salt and pepper. Cover with beans, potatoes, onions, garlic and cloves.
Mix mushroom soup and 1 cup water together in a small bowl, then pour this over the rest of the casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Bake in covered pan (cover with foil, if needed) at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken-crouton casserole
directions: Mix croutons and butter together and press half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crouton mixture; top with remaining croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.
Good way to use your leftover chicken or turkey.

title: lefse
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour when hot.
Let cool well, then add flour.
Chill before rolling.
Roll out a heaping tablespoonful of dough about the size of an egg on a well floured surface to a 6-inch circle.
Roll out thin.
Use a cast-iron frypan.
Bake on both sides at medium-high heat.
Bake until lightly brown on both sides.
Serve with butter.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Bring the water, onion and rice together. Add broccoli and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add rice and stir until all rice is all wet. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and soup. Stir into casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
The last 5 minutes baking, sprinkle top with bread crumbs and bake with lid on.

title: fabulous caramel clusters
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Melt caramels with water in 2 1/2 to 3 -quart heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently, until smooth.
Add cereal and pecans.
Mix lightly until well coated. Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 minutes, stirring after 15 minutes.
Turn out onto greased wax paper.
Cool thoroughly.
Break apart.
Makes about 10 cups.
tags: bite size crispy rice cereal squares

title: coconut cream delight
directions: Mix flour and margarine together, forming crust.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.
Beat pudding and cold milk together until thickened; set aside.
Mix cream cheese with half of Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust.
Spread pudding on top of cream cheese mixture. Cover with rest of Cool Whip; sprinkle with toasted coconut; refrigerate.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan with vegetable oil.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of hot cornbread to make a melted cheese topping. Serve with pinto beans.

title: rabbit fricassee
directions: Cut up rabbit into serving size pieces.
Soak in a solution of 1/4 cup vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt and enough water to cover the rabbit for 3 hours.
Drain and dry.
Sprinkle pieces with monosodium glutamate.
Cover and allow to stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Mix 2 teaspoons salt and pepper, saffron and oregano.
Rub into the meat.
Fry rabbit slowly in 1-inch of bacon drippings until browned on all sides.
Place onion in a casserole followed by rabbit.
Pour 1 tablespoon vinegar in 1/2 cup water over the rabbit.
Cover tightly and bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: turkey burgers on the grill
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into patties.
This can be used with hamburger or can be made into a loaf.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in 1 gallon of water in 2 1/2 to 3 gallon glass jar or container.
Add zucchini and soak 24 hours.
Pour off lime water and rinse 10 minutes until water runs clear.
Allow to drain on paper towel, terry cloth or screen for 3 hours.
In a large stainless steel or enamel kettle, add vinegar and sugar; stir well.
Add pickling spice.
Add zucchini and let stand for 24 hours.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 35 minutes.
Add green food coloring, if desired.
Fill jars, cap and enjoy.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and pat into a 15 x 10 inch baking sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven and cool completely.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together cream cheese, sour cream, and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread mixture on top of cooled crust.
Top with mixed vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Cut into 2-inch squares and serve.
Makes 35 squares.

title: ratatouille *
directions: Dice eggplant, zucchini, onion and green pepper.
Combine with rest of ingredients in large pan and bring to a boil (covered). Then uncover and let simmer on very low flame for approximately 3 hours, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: healthy spinach roll-ups
directions: In saucepan cook noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Thoroughly drain spinach, pressing out excess liquid. Combine egg whites, spinach, cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, oregano, basil and garlic powder.
Spread one-eighth of mix on each noodle.
Loosely roll up jelly roll style, starting with short edge.
Place, seam side down, in casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over rolls.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in greased 12-inch pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes until golden brown at 350°.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add all your vegies and simmer for 2 hours. You can add more water.
Put a couple bouillon cubes in.
I put enough water to make as much broth that's needed.
I don't use salt, but I put a little pepper and onion powder or to your taste.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Mix in order given. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven. Remove from the oven and pour on topping.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands.
Roll dough into balls.
Brown in a 375° oven.

title: baklava
directions: Grind walnuts very fine.
Add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Grease a 10 x 15-inch pan with melted butter.
Place 4 filo in pan.
Brush each with melted butter.
Sprinkle every thin layer with meat mixture.
Cover with 4 filo.
Brush as before.
Continue procedure until pan is full.
Brush top filo generously with melted butter and put pastry into individual pieces before baking.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: beans and franks cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Combine pork and beans, franks, green pepper, onion and chili powder and pour into prepared dish.
Stir cornmeal mix, milk, egg and oil until smooth and pour evenly over bean and franks.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until cornbread is golden.

title: delicious corn dish
directions: Put all ingredients in covered casserole and bake at 325° until bubbly, stirring twice. Bake approximately 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry cheesecake tarts
directions: With foil baking cups in muffin tins, place one vanilla wafer or gingersnap in each. Cream remaining ingredients, except cherry pie filling, until smooth. Fill cups 1/2 full and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until barely beginning to brown. Top with cherry pie filling or other topping, if desired. Makes 15-20 tarts.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Green
onions, fresh mushrooms, green peppers, radishes, cauliflower, broccoli, tomatoes (first de-seed).

title: lemon herbed salmon
directions: In a bowl, combine bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, cheese, thyme, lemon zest and salt; mix well.
Add 4 tablespoons of butter and toss lightly to coat; set aside.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces. Combine with onion and cheese; refrigerate.

title: chicken or steak dinner in foil
directions: On large pieces of foil, place chicken or steak, salted and peppered.
Thinly slice potatoes over meat, then carrots.
Mix soups and spoon over vegetables.
Top with frozen peas.
Close foil securely.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chinese macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve.

title: pressed cookie mold recipe
directions: Mix and knead dough.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Lay out for 4 or 5 days.
Use straw to punch a hole in mold if it is to hang.

title: german pancake(sometimes called dutch babies)
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add flour, milk and salt, mix well.
Add the melted butter.
Put in greased cake pan (or I use iron skillet). Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until well browned, about 6-inches high.
When baked, cut into wedges and serve.
I usually double or triple this recipe.

title: bagels and cream cheese
directions: Toast bagels.
Spread with cream cheese.
Layer salmon, onions and capers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sausage corn bread
directions: Make corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Stir in sausage and Italian seasoning.
Pour into a 8x8x12 baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: On bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, place single layer of whole graham crackers.
Beat pudding, milk and Cool Whip until smooth. Pour half of pudding mixture over graham cracker lining.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: *You may use your own frozen yeast dough.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time.
Combine preserves and buttermilk in a separate bowl.
To butter mixture, alternately add flour and preserves mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts; grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix and cook in enamel container until thickens, stirring often to prevent sticking. Cook on low heat.
Put in hot sterile jars and seal or eat.

title: almond clusters
directions: Melt together in microwave chocolate chips and Candi-Quick according to directions on chocolate chip package.
Add roasted almonds and drop by teaspoonful on wax paper to set.
Very delicious.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the milk and pudding mix on low speed for 2 minutes; beat in vanilla.
Fold in 3 cups whipped topping. Pour 1 1/3 cups of the pudding mixture into pie crust.
Layer with banana slices and remaining pudding mixture.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Garnish with additional banana slices, if desired.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: bell pepper stuffed
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Add milk to mushroom liquid to total of 1/2 cup.
Combine meat, mushroom (sliced), bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and egg.
Remove end and seeds from peppers.
Cut into three 1-inch rings.
Place green peppers in a shallow baking dish and pack meat mixture into pepper rings. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Combine catsup and grated cheese and spoon over patties.
Continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix together; place in a greased casserole.
Top with crushed potatoes chips and shredded American or Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Enjoy!

title: juanita's spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach in salted water.
Drain.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in large buttered baking pan, spread reserved crumbs over top.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, or until heated through.

title: hot punch
directions: Put the apple cider and cranberry
juice cocktail in a 30-cup percolator. In basket, put the brown sugar, cinnamon sticks, salt and whole cloves. Perk and serve.

title: easy italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans. Separate eggs.
Place yolks in large mixing bowl.
Place whites in a small bowl and beat until stiff.
To egg yolks, add cake mix and butter.
Mix well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add to mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Blend well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Gently stir in pecans and coconut.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes then remove to serving platter.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: potato soup
directions: In large soup pot, saute bacon until clear.
(Do not brown!) Add leeks, spring and yellow onions, bouillon (use more if needed) and flour.
Bring to simmer, stirring occasionally, until onions are clear (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Add potatoes and creams.
Cook at a gentle simmer about 50 minutes to 1 hour, until potatoes are soft.
Remove from heat.

title: "ham glaze"
directions: In electric mixer, beat in order given.
Bake ham in 325° oven with ginger ale or beer in bottom of pan for 20 minutes to the pound.
When ham is cooled, remove all fat.
Wipe ham dry and crisscross in diamonds.

title: caramel walnut bars(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts. Reserving 2 cups of crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup bread crumbs.
Shape into 15 (2-inch) balls.
Roll in remaining crumbs, coating well.
Flatten balls into small patties. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in a skillet and fry patties 5 minutes on each side.
Add more oil as needed.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper.

title: baked duck
directions: Season duck with salt, red pepper, black pepper, white pepper, thyme, oregano and basil.
Sprinkle onion and apple with cinnamon. Stuff into duck cavity.
Cover each duck with 4 strips of bacon.

title: no-cook play dough
directions: In bowl, mix together flour and salt.
Stir in oil, water and food coloring.
Add more water if necessary to form a soft, pliable dough.
This keeps well in airtight bag.

title: feather rolls
directions: Heat milk, be sure not to burn it.
Add shortening, salt and sugar to milk; cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs to mixture when mix is cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to milk mixture.
Stir in 4 cups flour; knead until smooth (about 5 minutes).
Add remaining flour.
Grease topp of dough and rise 2 hours.
Punch down dough and work out rolls, let rise 1 1/2 hours. Bake at
375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350°.
When half done, add 1 can tomato sauce.
Pour over loaf and finish baking.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder, one spoonful at a time, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir in crushed pineapple and juice; blend well.
Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven. Turn oven to 325° and bake 1 1/2 hours, or until top springs back when touched lightly.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Fold in pumpkin, spices and salt. Pour into crust.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: beef roast
directions: Put beef roast in roaster.
Blend Coca-Cola and mushroom soup; pour over roast. Sprinkle with onion soup. Bake at 300° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours or until nice and tender.

title: caramel pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Fold in the whipped topping. Spread half into the pie crust.
Drizzle with half the caramel topping.
Combine coconut and pecans.
Sprinkle half over the caramel.
Repeat layers and chill or freeze until ready to serve.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water and set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, salt and hot water.
Cook and stir in double boiler until thickened.
Pour over gelatin and mix well.
Combine beaten egg whites, sugar and nutmeg.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg white mixture.
Add rum, if desired.
Pour into 9-inch baked crust.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
(For best results, do not double the recipe.)

title: caramel rolls
directions: Using a well-greased Bundt pan, sprinkle bottom with nuts. Arrange rolls; sprinkle with pudding mix and brown sugar.
Drizzle melted butter over rolls.
Set out on counter and cover with wax paper or in oven overnight and bake in the morning about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve cherry and unflavored gelatin completely in boiling water.
Let cool slightly, then stir in cranberry sauce, drained pineapple and celery.
Pour into a 6-cup mold that has first been rinsed under cold water and chill until firm.
At serving time, dip mold briefly in a pan of hot water to loosen.
Unmold onto chilled plate.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter; pat into pie plate.
Mix well the yogurt and jello; pour into crust and freeze.
Add Cool Whip before serving.
Cut into 8 servings.

title: deer sausage
directions: Grind all meat together and hand mix spices into meat.
Make patties and freeze. Fry patties as desired until done.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix eggs and salad oil together and stir into dry ingredients; do not beat. Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon batter into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Allow cakes to cool in pans for 10 minutes after removing from oven.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting (recipe follows).

title: italiano meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef in a large skillet; drain. Add green pepper; cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in water, tomato paste and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Grate egg yolks finely and set aside.
Chop onion, egg white, celery and cheese.
Mix with spinach in a bowl.
Add salt, vinegar and Tabasco.
Mix in mayonnaise just before serving.
Garnish with egg yolk.
Great potluck salad.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Chill sweet potatoes.
Combine dry ingredients, add potatoes and eggs.
For small balls and fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: jim dandy cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar.
Add in egg, milk, soda, salt and flour.
Melt chocolate with milk.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool and ice with favorite chocolate icing.

title: california pasta salad
directions: Drain artichokes, reserving marinade in a large bowl.
Add vinegar, mustard, lime juice, garlic, salt, marjoram and pepper; mix well.
Add artichokes, pasta, nuts, cucumber and tomato; toss to coat.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Garnish with avocado slices.
Serves 6.

title: indian popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients until it is in a fine crumbly texture. Then add warm water until mixture sticks together.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Soak oatmeal in boiling water for 20 minutes, then mix in the oleo, brown sugar and salt.
Mix yeast, warm water and white sugar, then mix with oatmeal mixture.
Add flours and knead.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-up biscuits
directions: Add the 7-Up and other ingredients.
Turn out in a little flour.
Knead 8 times.
Bake in oven at 450°.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Grease muffin pan and spoon out into individual cups.
Cook at 425° until brown.

title: quick & easy nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour 9x13in. baking pan. Base: Stir together in a medium bowl until well mixed; dry cake mix, 3/4 c. melted butter, 3/4 c. pecans. Press mixture evenly into the bottom of prepared pan.

title: six-cup salad
directions: Mix together oranges, coconut, marshmallows, pineapple, fruit cocktail and sour cream.
Let set for 30 minutes or more before serving.

title: egg nog bread pudding
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and cut bread into 1-inch chunks. Coarsely chop chocolate and toss with bread in a pan.
In large bowl, whisk eggnog, half and half, sugar, coffee and eggs.
Pour this over the bread and dot with butter.
Set dish in large roaster and place on oven rack.
Fill roaster with water halfway up the side of baking dish.
Bake 1 hour until a knife blade comes out clean.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar serving warm with ice cream topping.
Oven temperature should be 325° for baking.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli.
Cut tops and some of the stems from broccoli, then wash and add other ingredients to the broccoli flowerets and stems.
Chill and serve.

title: lupias
directions: Mix all ingredients, except won ton wrappers. Separate several won ton wrappers, then place 1 tsp. or 2 tsp. of meat mixture in to the center of the wrapper. Fold the mixture to where the meat is all covered. Deep fat fry.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and cube potatoes and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with dry salad dressing mix.
Top with small pats of butter.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes to an hour.

title: deer valley's french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar; let sit until bubbly.
Add oil, 2 cups flour and salt; beat.
Gradually add remainder of flour until you have a soft dough.
Knead well.
Let rice once; shape.
Slash tops with knife.
Let rise again after shaping into 2 long loaves.
Bake at 400° until brown.
If soft crust is desired, brush with melted butter.

title: best banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add condensed milk and sour cream, then add Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.
Layer dish with cookies and bananas, then pudding mix.
Layer again.

title: candy mints
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and beat at high speed until well blended.
Knead until smooth.
Shape mints in candy molds. Then place on cookie sheets which have been covered with paper towels.
Cover with paper towels.
Leave overnight to set.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients. Dip bread in mixture and fry in melted butter. Makes 4 slices.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and mix with salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Squeeze dry.
Add pepper and carrots to cabbage.
Combine vinegar, sugar, water, celery and mustard seed in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage and mix.
Put into plastic freezer boxes and freeze.

title: cheesy garlic crisps
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine margarine and garlic.
If using tortillas, cut into 6 wedges.
Brush one side of each slice of rye bread or both sides of tortillas with some of the margarine mixture.
Place on a baking sheet in 350° oven for 5 minutes. Turn over and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes more or until crisp and brown.
Makes 24.

title: okra and fresh corn casserole
directions: Wash and drain okra.
Combine 2 tablespoons butter and the okra in heavy skillet.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, until okra is no longer sticky.
Cut corn from cob.
Put okra and corn in alternate layers in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa together thoroughly.
Spread mixture onto platter.
Chop lettuce and sprinkle on top of cream cheese and salsa mixture.
Chop tomatoes and sprinkle on top of lettuce.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over entire platter.
Use tortilla chips with Taco Salad Dip and enjoy!

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a greased casserole.
Saute onion in butter; add sour cream, water, eggs (which have been slightly beaten), salt and pepper.
Pour over the potatoes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Temperature may be raised the last 5 minutes if a brown topping is desired.

title: chile con carne
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Quickly saute onions, sliced, until transparent.
Add the hamburg and barely cook.
Add all ingredients together except beans.
Put into pot and simmer 45 minutes or longer.
Add beans and heat.

title: conch fritter
directions: Grind conch or chop finely.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Heat fryer oil.
Place mixture by spoonful into oil. Cook until golden brown.
Serve with cocktail, tartar or honey mustard sauce.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Soak cut up cucumbers for 7 days in a strong, salt water. Wash cucumbers.
Soak overnight in alum (use alum size of egg). Dissolve alum in water (enough to cover cucumbers).
Drain.
Soak for 6 hours in white vinegar.
Drain off vinegar and throw away. Layer cucumbers in jug with sugar, pickling spices, etc.
Best served cold.

title: jane's marvelous mushrooms
directions: Remove caps and set mushrooms aside.
Chop stems.
Melt butter in a small skillet and saute stems and onions until tender.
Add bread cubes, cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly until lightly brown.
Add salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Fill mushroom caps with the mixture and place in a shallow baking dish.
Pour the wine around the mushrooms and a little over each. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese and bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.
Enjoy!

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Combine cauliflower, onion, garlic, chicken-flavored bouillon, thyme and water in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes or until cauliflower is tender.
Spoon half of cauliflower mixture into container of an electric blender; blend until smooth.
Repeat procedure with remaining mixture; set aside.
Heat oil in a 2 quart heavy saucepan over medium-low heat. Add flour, stirring well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add cauliflower mixture to milk mixture.
Add pepper, if desired.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring often.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: egg yolk paint
directions: Beat water with egg yolk.
Divide mixture into 4 or more small containers.
Add different food colors to each.
Paint cookies before baking.

title: hot chicken and rice dish
directions: Combine and heat until hot.
Serve with green salad.

title: christmas relish
directions: Put salt over ground up vegetables. Let stand 1 hour. Mix well, rinse and squeeze out liquid. Heat vinegar, sugar and spices and pour over vegetables. Pour into jars. No need to seal. (I seal mine.)

title: creamy dill sauce
directions: Mix.
Stir over low heat.
Use on any hot vegetables.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa and oil.
Melt chocolate and shortening together; cool.
Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend in chocolate mixture, then flour.
Next add nuts.
Pour in well-greased 8-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: pasta basilica
directions: Saute garlic and tomato in olive oil over medium heat unti tender.
Add wine and simmer until reduced slightly (5 to 10 minutes).
Add basil; stir and remove from heat.
Spoon over cooked pasta, then sprinkle cheese on top to taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pesto cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rub 1 tablespoon butter over the bottom and sides of a 9-inch diameter spring-form pan.
Mix bread crumbs with 2 tablespoons grated cheese.
Coat pan with crumb mixture. Using an electric mixer, beat cream cheese, Ricotta, remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan, salt and cayenne in a large bowl until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Transfer half of mixture to a medium bowl.
Mix pesto into remaining half. Pour pesto mixture into prepared pan; smooth top.
Carefully spoon plain mixture; gently smooth top.
Sprinkle with pine nuts.
Bake cake until center no longer moves when pan is shaken, about 45 minutes.
Transfer to rack and cool completely.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Run small sharp knife around pan sides to loosen cheesecake, if necessary.
Release pan sides from cheesecake.
Transfer cheesecake to platter.
Garnish with fresh basil sprigs.
Surround with crackers and serve.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix together first six ingredients.
Add potatoes.
Mix 2 tablespoons butter with corn flakes.
Put potato mixture in buttered baking dish.
Spread out evenly.
Sprinkle the corn flakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover while baking.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add salt, sugar, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cream together onion, cream cheese and sour cream.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, layer noodles, meat mixture and sour cream mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix according to directions on box and make into 3 layers.

title: apricot rolls
directions: Roll out on flour and sugar. Cut into squares. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Use Baker's apricot for filling.

title: no peek stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a deep casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Remember, no peeking.
Enjoy.

title: cook while you sleep cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy, add salt and cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and chocolate morsels (Nestle).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Put in oven and turn off heat immediately.
Do not open door for at least 8 hours.
Carefully remove cookies from foil.
Yields about 40 or 50 cookies.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour.
Knead in enough flour to form a smooth dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shape.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: "stuff" (easy casserole)
directions: Press ground chuck into 9 x 12-inch pan; salt and pepper. Spread onions over meat, then Veg-All, salt and pepper.
Spread soup over Veg-All, then add Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
During baking time you will have to pour off excess liquid.
Add grated cheese, if desired, about last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Dice apricots into 1/4-inch pieces.
Place apricots and orange juice in small saucepan over low heat and bring to a boil; continue cooking 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: nutted wild rice
directions: Place rice in strainer and rinse in cold water.
Put rice in heavy saucepan.
Add 5 1/2 cups chicken stock.
Bring to rapid boil.
Reduce to simmer and cook uncovered for 45 minutes (check in 30 minutes to make sure it isn't getting too soft).
Put thin towel in colander.
Drain rice and place in bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Needs to stand 2 hours to develop.
Serve at room temperature.

title: butterscotch apple dip
directions: Combine chips, salt and milk in saucepan over low heat.
Cook and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and cinnamon.
Serve warm for dipping sliced apples.
May refrigerate up to 3 weeks.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers, peppers and dill in jars.
Bring remaining ingredients (except the alum) to a rolling boil.
Pour into jars over cucumbers, then add the alum to each jar and seal.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald meal; stir in butter, salt and egg.
Add baking powder and milk.
Turn into a greased baking dish and bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot with butter.

title: steak and rice casserole
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces; salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour and fry in 1/2-inch of oil in skillet.
Put raw rice in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put meat on top.
Chop onion and put on meat.
Brown flour.
Add water to make thin gravy.
Pour over meat and rice. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.
Can add bell peppers, mushrooms or tomatoes.

title: chicken in creamy mushroom sauce
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Add mushrooms and cook (if fresh mushrooms for five minutes).
Remove chicken and mushrooms.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Pour in broth and half & half.
Cook until thick.
Add mushrooms and chicken.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
I used my slow cooker.

title: 24 hour lettuce salad
directions: Add sugar to taste to the mayonnaise.
Place ingredients in the order given in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(I like to use double of everything except lettuce.)
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: fiesta roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tortillas.
Spread thinly and evenly on each tortilla and roll up.
Put in freezer to chill and then slice and serve.
For a change, you can also use taco seasoning instead of the dressing mix.

title: marble drops
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine with sugar and oil in a bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each one.
Add vanilla.
Mix.
Chill several hours.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Do not flatten out.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix flour and sugar (powdered) in bowl. Stir in just enough butter with fork until all flour is moistened and dough cleans the side of bowl. Pat in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown. Cool.

title: "easy coconut cake"
directions: Combine the first three ingredients; let stand overnight. Next day, prepare cake mix according to package directions, making 2 layers.
Split layers.
Spread layers with coconut mixture and refrigerate 2 to 3 days.
(The reader will note that this cake "gets better every day".
"Yummy.")

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk and cheese; set aside.
Sprinkle chicken with flour, salt and seasonings.
Dip chicken into buttermilk mixture, coating both sides and using all of the mixture.
Now, coat chicken with bread crumbs.
In skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken and cook, turning once, until brown on both sides.

title: rocky road fudge pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, chocolate and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
If mixture seems thin, chill, then beat until fluffy.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Spoon into pie crust; chill until firm.
Serve garnished with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, lemon juice and margarine.
Slowly cook to boiling, cook 2 minutes.
Set aside. When cooled, add sour cream and beat thoroughly.
Pour into an 8-inch baked pie shell or crumb crust and serve with whipped cream.
Also very good with 1 cup well drained crushed pineapple instead of lemon juice.

title: toasted butter pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans in 1/4 cup butter for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream 1 cup of butter. Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into three layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagna roll-up
directions: Cook lasagna in salted, boiling water until just tender. Drain.
Place in cold water.
Drain spinach well and mix with Ricotta cheese, salt, pepper, nutmeg, egg and Parmesan cheese. Drain noodles and pat dry with paper towels.
Cut ham slices in half, lengthwise.
Place on noodles.
Spread each with spinach mix. Roll up noodles and place on sides in 9x13 inch baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over lasagna and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until done.
Serve 10.

title: wonton soup
directions: Place in a bowl, the ground pork, green onions, ginger, soy sauce, 1 teaspoon sesame oil, Chinese wine, sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Mix together well and set aside.
Heat stock in wok and bring to the boil.
Season with salt and pepper, wrap 1/2 teaspoon of pork mixture into each wonton wrapper.
Close tightly and drop into stock.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Wontons usually rise to the surface when cooked.
Add 1/2 teaspoon sesame oil and stir in. Garnish with green onion or fresh coriander.

title: reese's peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare brownies as directed on package.
Place mixture in pan. Press peanut butter cups into mixture so that tops are even with batter.
Bake 35 minutes and let cool.
Cut!

title: broccoli-rice malange
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and sprinkle on top the butter, cheese and paprika.
Bake in moderate oven until bubbly.

title: blueberry muffins with streusel topping
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/3 cup sugar in a large bowl, mixing well.
Reserve 2 tablespoons mixture and set aside.
Make a well in center of remaining flour mixture.
Combine egg, milk and oil; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Combine blueberries and reserved 2 tablespoons flour mixture, tossing to coat.
Stir blueberries into batter just until blended. Spoon the batter into greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.

title: herbed pinwheels
directions: Mix herbs into softened margarine.
Place 2 large sections of crescent rolls side by side on floured board.
Roll to 10 x 12-inch.
Spread herb oleo to cover dough.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Slice to fill 12 greased muffin tins.
Beat 1 egg with 1 tablespoon water.
Apply mixture to top and sides of rolls.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: oreo mint shiver
directions: Chop up cookies.
Place milk and ice cream in blender.
Add chopped cookies.
Cover.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Serve immediately.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Place oil in frying pan with garlic.
Simmer.
Drain the juice from cans of clams into a cup.
Pour 1/2 cup of clam juice into pan.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add rest of clam juice, clams, parsley and water.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over linguini.

title: meat loaf superb
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, 3 tablespoons soy sauce and 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup; mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Place in 9 x 5-inch pan.

title: cheezy potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in large casserole dish for 45 minutes.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You will need foil cupcake holders.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Mix and add alternately flour and baking powder with sour cream.
Dust greased Bundt pan with 1/2 mixture of sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour half the batter in pan.
Sprinkle rest of cinnamon mixture on top and pour remainder of batter in pan.
Bake 1 hour or more at 325°.

title: light broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: rice and chicken
directions: Put 2 tablespoons olive oil in 5-quart pan.
Turn heat on high.
Saute onions and garlic for 2 minutes, turning frequently. Cut chicken in 1/4 size pieces, season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add chicken to pan and saute each side 5 minutes until slightly browned.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil and add bell pepper and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slice and add mushrooms, black olives, peas, carrots, chopped tomato with own liquid and tomato sauce.
Cook, covered, for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add rice and 3 cups of water.
Turn to high heat and stir until all ingredients are mixed well.

After water has evaporated from top of rice, reduce heat to medium and cover for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to low and turn rice from bottom to top, starting at center, cover and cook on low for additional 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with brown sugar and vanilla.
Add peanuts.
Serve with apple slices.

title: snow logs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate several hours.
Roll into logs by hand and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Roll while hot in confectioners sugar.
Cool slightly, then roll again.
A Christmas/Hanukkah favorite.

title: nacho spread
directions: Mix the refried beans and taco seasoning and add liquid from green chilies until mixture is spreadable.
Spread on a platter (1/4 to 1/2-inch thick layer).
Then layer remaining ingredients. Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve with nachos.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar, flour and juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Stir well. Put in a 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Put on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham croquettes
directions: Combine ham, potatoes, egg, onions and parsley. Add salt and pepper. Shape into balls. Roll in bread crumbs. Brown in hot oil, turning often, until golden brown.

title: biscuits (mayonnaise)
directions: Stir all ingredients well. Put into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400°.
Brown as desired.

title: raspberry sherbet dessert
directions: For crust, combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place pan in the freezer while preparing sherbet mixture.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Mix the liquid ingredients and add them gradually to the dry.
Fill well-greased molds 2/3 full. Steam 3 1/2 hours.
Butter the cover before placing it on the mold.
Baking powder tins may be used for molds.
When done, remove the lids and brown in oven, if desired.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together.
Add ginger ale and soda water as close to serving time as possible.
Serves 30 people.

title: washboards
directions: Shape dough into 3 rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Chill several hours or overnight until firm.
Slice with sharp knife into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix mayonnaise and soup mix and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Pour bread crumbs and cheese mix over casserole after it's been in the oven 5 to 10 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, ginger and salt.
Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Beat in egg; blend with molasses.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture.
Beat thoroughly; stir in water.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch square pan 40 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: crystal light lemon pie
directions: Mix Crystal Light and pudding and milk with mixer until slightly thickened.
Add
Cool Whip.
Pour in to the crust and chill until set.

title: farmers pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo, shortening and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk and flavoring to batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Reduce to 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 3 minutes; turn out on foil and wrap to cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Put shrimp in a bowl and mash with a fork; add sour cream, cream cheese, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: crispy onion chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonstack cooking spray.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over chicken.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Sprinkle evenly over chicken. Press mixture down gently into the mayonnaise.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop ham in food processor until fine.
Mix all ingredients. Roll into one or two balls.
Roll in parsley flakes, then in crushed pecans.

title: old time fruit salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and butter in saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until thickened stirring constantly. Refrigerate until cool.
Peel, core and chop apples.
Place fruit, nuts and marshmallows in a large bowl and add cooked dressing.
Mix well.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer or spoon until smooth. Spoon into greased muffin pan. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Cook 2 cups of berries with sugar, cornstarch and water over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice, butter and remaining berries.
Pour in pie shell and cool. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: mock baked steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and water.
Press in oblong pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares; roll in flour and brown in skillet over medium heat.
Place in baking dish.
Mix soup and water; pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gloria's italian chicken
directions: Wash, salt and pepper chicken pieces. Leave a little wet. Roll in shredded Parmesan cheese (or that from a can). Heat a small amount of olive oil. Chop a clove or 2 of garlic into the oil; then add the chicken and brown. When the chicken is well browned on both sides, add the wine*; cover and cook until done, about 20 minutes. When chicken is done, add the mushrooms and stir. You can also pour in 1/4 cup more wine at this point if you want more flavor. Serves about 6. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: open-faced cucumber tea sandwiches
directions: Soften cheese; add milk and dressing mix.
Spread on rye bread slices.
Top with cucumbers and olive slices.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain off fat.
Mix soup, seasoning and milk; add to meat.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan place a layer of tortillas, meat and cheese.
Repeat until all of the meat mixture is used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine in a Dutch oven until crisp-tender.
Arrange chicken in a layer over vegetables followed by spaghetti noodles.
Combine soup, broth, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over spaghetti, making sure all spaghetti is moistened.
Scatter mushrooms on top.
Cover, bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally 15 to 20 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Serves 4.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix avocados with cream cheese, garlic salt, hot sauce and lemon juice.
Spread in flat dish.
Chill.
Spread (room temperature) sour cream, gently over avocados, then pour picante sauce over this.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla and beat. Add sifted dry ingredients and beat.
Stir in oats, nuts and coconut.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in sugar; flatten slightly on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add cabbage, carrots, soy sauce, pepper and salt to taste.
Try not to cook the cabbage and carrots too long.
Sit off heat.
In a large skillet, heat oil on medium-high to medium heat.
Take egg rolls out one at a time. Place beef mixture in center of roll.
Fold up like a baby's diaper.
Wet one end to hold in place.
Place in hot oil until golden brown.
Turn over and brown the other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Dip in sweet and sour sauce.

title: breakfast squares
directions: Break bread into pieces and put into bottom of sprayed 9 x 13 pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top of bread. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes. This may be prepared the night before. Just cover and place in the refrigerator.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Roll out biscuits until flat.
Spread tomato sauce on top of each biscuit.
Brown beef and sausage together.
Drain well. Sprinkle meat on top of tomato sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: croutons
directions: Cube bread in 1/4-inch squares.
Mix oil, Mrs. Dash and garlic salt; toss with bread.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Mix around 2 times.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; cream well.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder and salt; add to mixture.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fiesta spread
directions: Brown beef with next three ingredients; drain excess fat.
Add next four ingredients.
Mash in beans.
Heat stirring frequently. Garnish with cheese and if desired, sliced olives.
Serve warm with Ritz crackers. Makes about 3 1/2 cups of spread.

title: seafood overtime
directions: Boil pasta shells until soft.
Drain over cold water.
Put pasta shells in a bowl that's large enough to accomodate you.
Boil eggs until done.
Cut eggs in small chunks.
Cut celery in small chunks.
Take all ingredients and mix in bowl with pasta shells. Once all ingredients are mixed, add red pepper.
Serve on crackers or in salad.

title: chicken taquitas
directions: Prepare chicken.
Saute garlic and green onions in Crisco oil. Stir in chicken.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, flour, cumin, oregano, chili powder and salt.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.

title: marlene's beef stew
directions: Brown stew meat really well in small amount of oil.
Put all the ingredients in with the stew meat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Then remove bay leaf and garlic.
Add 6 carrots and cut in 2-inch lengths.
Pare and halve 6 small potatoes and add 6 small onions.
Add to meat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add 1 cup frozen peas or drained canned peas.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Brown 1/2 cup sugar (in heavy, 6-inch skillet) and add to mixture.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until brown sugar dissolves and thickens.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Brown in a 350° oven.

title: heath bar cake
directions: While cake is hot, punch holes in top.
Pour milk and topping over top of cake.
Let set overnight or 3 or 4 hours.
Crush candy bars.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Put on top of cake.
Eat and enjoy.

title: skewered scallops and shrimp
directions: Prepare hot grill. Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap half-strip of bacon around each scallop.

title: chocolate-nut-zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Let cool; grease well 10-inch tube pan.
Sift dry ingredients together. Set aside.
At high speed in large bowl of mixer, beat eggs until thick; add sugar; beat well.
Add salad oil and cooled chocolate; beat well.
At low speed, add dry ingredients; mix until smooth. Add zucchini and nuts with wooden spoon; stir well.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly. Add vinegar. Mix well. Slowly add water. Cook until thickened. If not thick enough, you can add 1 1/2 teaspoons cornstarch mixed with water.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Brown in small amount of oil. Season with garlic powder and onion powder.
Cut green pepper into strips and add to steak.
Add water, bouillon cubes and soy sauce to taste.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add tomatoes and simmer a little longer; thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over rice.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips and margarine with Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
In large bowl, combine marshmallows and nuts.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Spread in foil-lined 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Chill 2 hours until firm.
Remove from pan and peel off foil.
Cut into squares.

title: 1-2 barbecue chicken(barbecue-style fried chicken)
directions: Arrange frozen chicken
pieces in a single layer in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic salt.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: rosemary peas and pasta
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Saute bacon, green onions and rosemary for 3 minutes.
Add frozen peas and cook covered for 5 minutes.
Drain. Process until pureed the cheese and milk.
Add to cooked pasta and bacon mixture.
Toss to coat.
Serves 4.

title: peach bread
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir only until moistened.
Stir in peaches, flavorings and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes for muffins or 1 hour for 2 loaves.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix everything all at once and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: irish mystery chicken
directions: In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, arrange slices of ham.
On each ham slice, place a chicken breast.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over chicken, covering completely.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over bed of wild rice with sauce.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 1 1/4 cups boiling water in bowl. Add raspberries and lemon juice, stirring until berries are thawed.
Chill until partially set.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt in bowl.
Fold in whipped cream gradually. Layer half the cream cheese mixture and raspberry mixture in pie shell.
Chill until set.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: strawberry champagne punch
directions: To Freeze Strawberries:
Wash and gently pat dry.
Arrange in a single layer on a cookie sheet; freeze until firm.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crush fresh ripe strawberries.
Mix with marshmallows.
Let stay in refrigerator overnight. Stir in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Serve immediately or serve frozen.

title: dream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen ornage juice and sugar.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Set until firm.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Divide cheese in half.
Grate 1 part and blend into sour cream.
Add seasonings sparingly to taste.
Blend together well. Crumble other half of cheese.
Fold into sauce.
Keep covered and refrigerated.
This dressing only improves with age, so can be made ahead.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, salt and water in a saucepan until a small amount forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Take out 1/2 cup of this mixture and cook the remainder until it forms a hard ball when tested in cold water.
Pour the 1/2 cup mixture slowly over the beaten egg whites.
Beat constantly.
Continue beating and add the remainder of the syrup when ready.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Continue beating until mass thickens and becomes heavy. Drop with a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Yields 48 servings.

title: honey graham squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In Dutch oven, melt peanut butter, honey, margarine and marshmallows.
Stir constantly until smooth. Stir in cereal and candy.
Press into pan with wet hands.
Cool completely before serving.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, beans, milk and vanilla. Add nuts and coconut. Mix all together and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes. Can wrap and freeze.

title: mexican quickie
directions: Cook hamburger and
chopped
onion
until meat is done. Remove as much grease
as	possible.
Add	the
taco sauce and water. Let simmer to blend
flavors.
In
the
bottom
of 9 x 13-inch pan place
the
tortilla
chips,
keeping
the
chips unbroken. Cover
chips with layer of shredded lettuce about 2 inches	deep. Pour
meat	mixture
over
lettuce and top with grated cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings.
Discard tips (or save for stock). Place chicken in large, plastic food storage bag.
Pour in teriyaki sauce.
Press air out of bag.
Close top securely. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight, turning bag over occasionally. Remove chicken from marinade; drain well.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Lightly coat about 1/3 of chicken with cornstarch.
Arrange in single layer in skillet and brown slowly on both sides.
Remove; place in single layer on rack placed on large baking sheet.
Repeat cooking procedure with remaining chicken, adding more oil if necessary.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve hot.

title: chicken cracker spread
directions: Mix together.
(Adjust onion & garlic powder to taste.)

title: spiced cranberries
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cranberries.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Simmer, covered, about 10 minutes.
Strain, add cranberries and cook without stirring until cranberries pop open. Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Or cool; then pack in desired containers and keep refrigerated.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: ninfa's margarita
directions: Combine above ingredients; shake.
Pour into salt-rimmed, ice filled glass.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cover bottom of crust with however many pecans you want to use.
Mix ingredients well and pour over pecans in crust.
Preheat oven.
Cook at 350° in the middle of the oven until pie puffs up, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.

title: blue monda dip
directions: Mix and chill before serving.
Serve with fresh vegetables, broccoli, cauliflower, bell peppers, etc.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Put margarine in last and beat. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Use your favorite icing, if desired.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box. Pour 3/4 mix in 9 x 11-inch cake pan (greased).
Set rest aside for cupcakes.
When cake is done, poke holes in top.
Boil pineapple and sugar until thickened and pour over cake.
Prepare vanilla pudding and pour over cake. Chill, put Cool Whip on top and serve.

title: easy apple strudel
directions: Blend flour and margarine as for pie.
Beat egg yolks; add to vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place the following layers in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish:

title: glazed pecans
directions: Boil all ingredients, except pecans, for 5 minutes.
Toss in pecans and stir.
Spread on wax paper and cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces. Sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper and place in a large soup pot. Add onions and enough water to cover. Cook until done, but not mushy. Add a sprinkling of parsley flakes. Stir in cream of celery soup and heat thoroughly. Cut cheese into small pieces and add to soup. Turn off heat and stir occasionally until cheese is melted. If desired, stir in lightly steamed broccoli florets as cheese melts.

title: waffle topping
directions: Cream the margarine. Add confectioners sugar and egg white. Cream to smooth.
Stir in crushed boysenberries.
Spoon on hot waffle.
No more butter necessary.

title: ham rolls
directions: Slice off top of rolls.
Layer ham and cheese on rolls. Replace roll tops.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour mixture on top of rolls.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: party jewel cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on package in two or three 9-inch round cake pans.
Cool cake.
Mix well beaten egg, sugar, Pet milk, vanilla, salt and butter in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 8 or 10 minutes.
Do not boil.
Take off of heat.
Stir in coconut, nuts and cherries.
Cool.
Spread cherry mixture between and on top of layers.
Decorate with nuts and cherries.
Chill 6 to 8 hours to let flavor blend.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Combine sour cream and all spices and seasonings.
Add chicken pieces and coat well.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight, covered.
When ready to cook, remove pieces of chicken from the sauce and roll in the bread crumbs.
Arrange in large baking dish. Sprinkle with melted butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve.

title: illinois, arkansas biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Should be a medium texture, not runny.
Pour onto floured surface.
Sprinkle flour over top of dough and pull flour around biscuit dough, then flip and pat down to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter and place onto greased cookie sheet. Grease tops.
Place into preheated oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brown bottoms, then put on top shelf and brown top about 5 to 10 minutes until done.
Serve hot.

title: fruit pound cake
directions: Cut pound cake in half lengthways.
Put fresh fruit in between cake.
Put top on.
Put Cool Whip over top and frost cake, then arrange fresh fruit on top of cake.

title: jody's peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water in iron skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat until vigorously boiling.
Add peanuts gradually so as not to reduce the boiling.
Cook until peanuts begin to pop. Add butter and cook until nuts are brown and mixture is caramel colored, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and salt.
Pour onto large, heavy-duty aluminum foil and spread thinly.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips, and butter on medium heat in a large pan.
Stir in Crispix cereal; until well coated. Put mixture in a large Ziploc bag and add powdered sugar.
Shake until well coated.
Refrigerate in air tight container until chilled.
Remove from refrigerator and store at room temperature.

title: pink lady dessert
directions: Combine Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and pie filling.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion, green and red pepper in large bowl. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup salt and cover with cold water; let stand 2 hours, then drain.
Press out excess liquid.
Sterilize jars. Combine sugar, vinegar and spices; heat to boiling.
Add drained vegetables; simmer 10 minutes.
Pack hot into 1/2 pint jars. Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Begin timing when the jars are placed in the boiling water.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken soup, chicken, sour cream, milk & chilies together. Set aside. Fry tortillas in small amount of oil until soft. Add about 1/4 cup of chicken mixture to each tortilla and top with about 1/4 grated cheese. Roll up and place seam side down in baking dish. Top with leftover chicken mixture and cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Yield: 18 enchiladas.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Stir in last.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until brown.
Takes longer to bake than regular corn bread.

title: cheesy beer sauce
directions: On medium-low heat combine cheese, milk, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, onion, garlic salt and margarine.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Garnish with jalapeno slices.
Serve as a dip over vegetables or whatever.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt butter in 9x13 pan in oven, In a bowl beat eggs, and remaining ingredients.
Por in pan, smooth out.
Bake at 350° for 35 min.

title: light chicken chili
directions: Lightly spray Dutch oven with Pam. Add chicken, onions and garlic. Cook over medium-high heat until chicken is just tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in broth, chilies, cumin and white pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, uncovered. Drain and rinse beans. Place 1/2 of the beans in a medium bowl and mash thoroughly. Stir mashed beans and remaining whole beans into chicken mixture. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Cut core of bread into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients (except bread) into covered bowl 24 hours prior to party. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Pour into bread shell and surround with bread pieces and pieces of fresh raw vegetables.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and pour over country style spareribs or chicken. Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: california cocoa
directions: In a quart bowl, combine sugar and cocoa.
Add about 1/2 cup of milk to make a paste.
Stir in the remaining milk, orange rind and almond extract.
Blend and microwave on high for 6-7 minutes. Pour into cups and add cinnamon sticks for stirring.

title: salisbury steak(incredible - the kids love it!)
directions: Work butter chips into meat, then parsley and then lemon juice mixed with water.
Form oval shape, 1 inch thick.
Rub broiler with butter.
Broil 3 inches from flame, 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn once.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and add onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Add water, ketchup, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
