Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: simon and garfunkel chicken
directions: Pound chicken; spread with 1/2 stick butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put slice of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Roll and tuck all ends.
Coat lightly with flour.
Dip in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Melt remaining butter and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting.
Add wine (Sauterne) and bake 20 minutes more.

title: tapioca-orange salad
directions: Cook pudding with the 3 cups liquid until thick.
Sprinkle and mix orange Jell-O into the pudding mixture.
Cool and refrigerate until chilled.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and oranges. Refrigerate.

title: chili cheese ball(ii. - m.s.)
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature to soften; combine cheese, lemon juice, garlic powder and red pepper; beat with rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Stir in nuts.
Shape in a ball.
Sprinkle with mixture of chili powder and paprika.
Chill. Before serving, let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onions, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Add to broccoli.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole that has been greased.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and crackers on top. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cube bread slices and mix with sugar and butter.
Set aside. Mix eggs, drained pineapple and milk together.
Combine with bread mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti with fresh tomatoes
directions: In frying pan, heat oil; cook garlic until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, basil and salt.
Heat through; do not overcook.
Cook vermicelli, drain and add tomato mixture and cheeses and serve.

title: homemade instant hot chocolate
directions: Sift all ingredients together.
Store in a covered jar.
Use 2 tablespoons for each cup. Fill with hot water, stirring as you mix.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and peanut butter. Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Add chocolate chips.
Form into small balls and flatten on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in 1/2 cup water (a little more if they absorb all of it) for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream, sugar, yolks, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Boil until thick.
Stir constantly or use double boiler to prevent scorching.
Pour into baked crust; top with meringue. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding beaten egg whites last.
Fry in deep fat, using a wire basket, like for donuts.
If fried in frying pan, use nonstick spray in pan.

title: crab dip
directions: Pour lemon juice over crabmeat.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Let stand 2 hours at room temperature.
Mix well, then toss in crabmeat and lemon juice, being careful not to break up crabmeat.
Warm and serve with dip-style corn chips.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Mix bread crumbs, walnuts and salt.
Beat eggs and stir in water.
Coat chicken with flour; dip in egg mixture and then in bread crumb mix.
Heat margarine and oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook chicken until golden brown (2 to 3 minutes), then place chicken in 13 x 9 x 1-inch baking dish (ungreased).
Pour broth into dish, then sprinkle chicken with cheese.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and spoon onto each chicken breast.
Cook uncovered at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Combine in pan sugar, butter and water.
Bring just to a boil. Add chocolate chips and vanilla extract.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add this mixture to chocolate batter.
Add 1 cup of nuts, if desired.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for approximately 50 minutes.
Makes moist, fudgy brownies.

title: helen's lemon delight
directions: Blend flour, oleo and 1/2 cup nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of the Cool Whip; spread over baked crust. Mix pudding with milk; pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread rest of Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Pour into a greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Melt one package chocolate chips for icing, spread on cake.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Add yeast to warm water; mix well, then add sugar to yeast. Cut Crisco and salt into flour; add beaten eggs to cooled milk and add yeast mixture.
Add this to flour mixture; stir hard and well. Refrigerate in covered container overnight.
Roll into round circle; cut into pie shape.
Roll from big end to small point. Let raise for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: good pie crust
directions: Beat egg and add water.
Mix well.
Mix all other ingredients and add egg and water mixture.
Yield: about 5 crusts.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and lemon.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Mix together sour cream and strawberries alternately.
Fold flour mixture and strawberry mixture into egg mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.
This is great warm with strawberries and whipped cream.

title: bacon tater bites
directions: You also need toothpicks.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix as listed.
Grease large cake pan.
Spread mixture in pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden and toothpick comes out clean.
Ice.
Refrigerate.

title: kathy's tomatoes florentine
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cooked, seasoned spinach.
Cut top off tomatoes; scoop out.
Fill with the spinach mixture.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, depending upon size.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Add broth from chicken to mushroom soup.
Saute celery and onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat at 350° until bubbling.

title: german slaw
directions: Grate vegetables.
In saucepan, bring vinegar, sugar, salt and mustard seed to rolling boil.
Pour over grated (chopped) vegetables.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients together except flour.
Don't make it sticky.
Then add flour, slowly.
Drop on a cookie sheet with an ice cream scoop.
Bake at 300° for 22 to 24 minutes.

title: low-fat fruit and cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve with assorted fresh fruit.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.
Contains 13 calories per tablespoon.

title: potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate thawed hash browns into shredded pieces; add egg.
Spray pan with vegetable spray and spread potatoes in pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove and add cheese, bake until the cheese melts.
Top with sour cream and bacon bits.
Cut into squares.

title: nadine's fruit punch
directions: Combine juices.
Add sugar to taste.
Add mint.
Chill.
Just before serving, add remaining ingredients.
Serve over ice.
Makes 75 punch cup servings.

title: a good child
directions: Take a child and give it a good home.
Add to this a good school system, a good church and a good community.
Add a dash of good friends and a large quantity of patience, understanding, genuine interest and, above all, love.
Let these ingredients blend together constantly, each adding its own flavor to the finished product.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Prepare green peppers, cut out tops and stems.
Discard stems. With a spoon, remove seeds from the inside of the peppers.
Rinse with cold water and set aside.
In small pan, melt butter and saute onion until golden.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Cook 2 cups of rice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage (3 to 4 minutes). Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in center of piece of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle onion over them.
Dot with butter and season to taste.
Seal foil around potatoes.
Wrap with a second piece of foil.
Cook directly in campfire or on outdoor grill until tender.
If not camping, baking may also be done in oven directly on rack at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, beating well. Stir in corn and milk.
Pour into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Stir once halfway through.
When done, pudding will be golden brown and a knife will come out clean.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; heat at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with a mild cracker for dipping.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wild apple cornbread
directions: Mix together in top of double boiler the cornmeal, sugar, salt, milk and margarine.
Set over hot water and cook 10 minutes.
Cool. Add eggs, soda (dissolved in water) and apples.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve with wild honey.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix dry cake and pudding; add eggs, oil and water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Remove from mixer and stir in grated chocolate, chips, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in square cake pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use recipe for 7-Minute Frosting, also in this book.

title: liz's apple cake
directions: Add sugar, eggs and oil; add salt, flour, cinnamon and soda. Stir well.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put package of yeast in the cup of lukewarm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Heat on stove until milk is scalded.
Cool this mixture; add egg and 1 cup flour to make a soft dough, then add yeast mixture and remaining flour. Mix, then turn onto floured board.
Knead and press out to about 1/2 inch thick; cut into 3 inch circles and sprinkle with melted oleo.
Turn in half and press together.
Let rise until doubled. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Grease tops with oleo when taken from oven.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all.
This is good on pork chops or steak.
Cook your meat. When almost done, pour over and simmer.

title: curry rice
directions: Fry your beef tips well.
Chop onion, carrots and potatoes in small stew size pieces.
Fill a pot with water.
Add the chopped onion, carrots and potatoes into the water.
Make sure that the water just covers the vegetables about 1/2 inch.
Add the beef and bring to a boil.
Add in curry; mix a small block at a time to produce the thickness of the stew juice you wish.
Now put 4 cups of rice in 6 cups of water.
Let boil.

title: an apple thing
directions: Mix and bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 1 small loaf.

title: hamburger zucchini bake
directions: Brown meat and mushrooms in butter or oil and drain.
Place in bottom of round 3-quart baking dish.
Slice zucchini thinly; lay Velveeta cheese slices over zucchini.
Lay second layer zucchini over cheese.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over zucchini. Sprinkle basil or dill over top of layers, a layer of bread stuffing or croutons over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yum-yum bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, peanut butter and butter in double boiler.
When melted, take off stove and put in marshmallows.
Stir, but don't melt them.
In buttered pan, place the desired amount of nuts.
Add mixture on top of nuts.

title: city chicken
directions: Remove fat from meat.
Cut into 1-inch squares and season with salt and pepper.
Alternate pieces of veal and pork on a skewer, five pieces to a stick.
Dip into mixture of beaten egg and milk; then roll into cracker crumbs.
Brown in hot fat.
Place in a baking dish.
Add a little water; cover.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Stir and heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over one large head of finely chopped cabbage, grated carrots, chopped green pepper and onion (if desired).
This Cole Slaw will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks (if it lasts that long).
This dressing is also good for a garden salad with lettuce, etc.

title: teriyaki beef or chicken
directions: Mix the marinade (first 6 ingredients).
Marinate steak or chicken (slice thinly into strips), green pepper slices and onion slices for a minimum of 4 hours.
You may marinate up to 12 hours. Brown the meat, onion and green peppers until tender.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato bread
directions: Combine butter, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add the potatoes and potato water, stirring well to blend.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Combine the yeast and warm water in a small bowl, stirring until dissolved, add to the potato mixture with 2 eggs. Stir in 3 cups flour to make a smooth batter.
Gradually add sufficient flour to make a soft dough that pulls away from the sides of the bowl.
Potatoes do make a sticky dough, but be careful not to add too much flour.
The less flour the more tender the bread.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and satiny, about 10 minutes.
Place in a warm buttered bowl, turning to coat top.
Cover with plastic wrap or a large towel and let rise until doubled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
If there is time, punch down the dough, knead in bowl and cover to rise again, about 45 minutes.

title: pecan drops
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and German chocolate in double boiler, stirring continuously until well mixed.
When melted, add pecans; stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Let cool overnight.

title: tri-color cookies
directions: You will need 3 (11 1/2 x 1/2-inch) pans for this recipe.

title: cavatina
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add spaghetti mixes, following the directions on package.
Can also add Parmesan cheese in the sauce, if desired.
Prepare macaroni, then mix with sauce.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Add some Colby and Cheddar cheese, scattered about.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add Certo.
Add green or red food coloring, if desired.
Can.

title: meat pie
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage in skillet with chopped up onion and sprinkle with a little oregano.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook rice. When cool enough to handle, mix with beef, sausage, salt, pepper and garlic. Trim cabbage and remove as many leaves as you can. Drop leaves in boiling water for a couple of minutes to soften and make pliable. Rinse with cold water to cool. Shape meat and rice mixture into oblong meatballs and wrap a cabbage leaf around each. Chop the remaining cabbage and put into
large turkey roaster, then place cabbage rolls on top.
Pour tomato sauce over the top and 1 quart of water.
Cover roaster with foil and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water and stir well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine refried beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce.
Spoon half of this mixture in bottom of prebaked pie shell.
Top with half of meat mixture, half of cheese and all of corn chips.
Repeat layers with remaining bean mixture, meat and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomato.
Serve with remaining taco sauce.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped potatoes and cheese
directions: Grease pan slightly with butter.
Dry potatoes with paper towel.
Spread 1/2 potatoes on the bottom of the dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese and butter; salt and pepper.
Spread remaining potatoes and cheese on top.
Pour milk into side of dish.
Bring to simmer over low heat.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Chop onions and peppers. Combine with cucumbers.
Salt and let stand 3 hours and drain. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in large container and bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers and heat slowly, but don't boil. Pack in jar while hot.

title: country style sausage links
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well.
Shape into 12 links.
Place a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add half of sausage links; cook 8 to 10 minutes, until browned, turning frequently.
Drain on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining links.

title: secret sirloin steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a large shallow dish and add steak.
Marinate in refrigerator about 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove steak from marinade; place on grill 5-inches from hot coals; grill about 8 to 12 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness.
Place the steak on a heated platter.
Combine last 3 ingredients and pour over steak. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cinnamon doughnut drops
directions: Heat 2 to 3 inches of oil to 375°.
In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in milk, oil, vanilla and egg with a fork, just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil, 5 to 6 at a time.
Fry 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; pat dry; remove stems.
Set caps aside.
Put oil, 1 slice bread (torn
in pieces), garlic salt, oregano, basil and bay leaf together in blender or food processor. Chop into fine pieces.
Tear remaining piece of bread and add with mushroom stems.
Continue until entire mixture is in very fine pieces.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and 1/4 cup nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake crust at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix powdered sugar, 1/2 cup Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread on cooled crust.
Cook pudding.
Cool and spread over the cheese in crust.
Spread the rest of the Cool Whip over the top and sprinkle with 1/4 cup nuts.
You can prepare this a day ahead of serving time, if you keep it in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender; cool and remove peelings. Grate coarsely and add 1 cup grated cheese, sour cream, butter and grated onion. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in casserole 30 minutes at 350°.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer each ingredient.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the egg whites, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper or carrot, milk, parsley, sage, thyme, basil, or oregano, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well. In a shallow baking dish pat mixture into a 6 X 3 X 1 1/2 inch loaf.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 40 to 50 minutes or till no pink remains.
Transfer meat loaf to a serving platter.
Spoon the barbecue sauce or catsup over the meat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: special vinaigrette
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients, except oil, with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper until smooth.
With blender motor running, add oil in a thin, steady stream.
Blend until dressing is slightly thickened.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into lightly greased 3-cup casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add the beef stock, carrots, potatoes, kidney beans, tomato paste, cabbage, oregano and thyme. Simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer 20 minutes more.
Yields 11 to 11 1/2 (1-cup) servings.

title: cherry supreme dessert
directions: Mix crumbs, butter and sugar well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan and save 1/2 for topping.
Whip the cream very well.
Add sugar and fold in marshmallows.
Spread layer of cream mixture over crumb mixture.
Add cherry pie mix and spread remainder of the cream mixture.
Sprinkle top with cracker mixture.
Chill, cut in serving pieces and serve.

title: gourmet cranberry sauce
directions: Dissolve the sugar in the orange juice, red wine and water. Bring to a boil and add the two packages cranberries that have been sorted, washed, drained and any stems removed.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes until all skins have popped.
Remove from heat; cool and refrigerate.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.
Can be prepared days ahead and double as a topping for vanilla ice cream, frozen yogurt or pudding.

title: zucchini surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together, spread in a greased baking dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lumpia(egg roll)
directions: Saute garlic and onion in a pot.
Add ground beef; season with salt.
Add carrot and green beans.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and cabbage.
Cook until done.
Drain and cool.
Wrap and roll tightly in lumpia wrapper.
Use 1 egg beaten to seal the wrapper.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Makes up to 28 to 32 pieces.
Serve hot and crispy.

title: esther's country steak
directions: Mix together and roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut in squares and brown.
Make a gravy and pour over meat.
Let heat through in oven at 350°.

title: green beans
directions: Layer the ingredients and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Put spare ribs in water with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Drain.
Start sauce 1 hour before meat is done.
Brown onions in butter, add brown sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, celery, water and catsup.
Pour sauce over meat and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Peel sweet
potatoes.
Cook
in
boiling,
salted water until tender, but
not mushy.
Drain and cool.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and
cinnamon
in a medium saucepan.
Stir in apricot nectar, hot
water	and
orange peel.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.	Remove from heat.
Stir in butter. Cool slightly; stir in pecans.
Cut sweet potatoes in half and place them in a
x 12-inch casserole.
Pour sauce over potatoes so all
are
glazed.
Bake,
covered,
at 375° for 25 minutes, until sauce is bubbling.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add walnuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan or individual tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Beat in egg yolks. Mix flour and soda in bowl.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until layers test done. Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread frosting between layers, sprinkling with pecans.
Spread remaining frosting over top and side of cake.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: herb meat loaf
directions: For a spicier sauce, mix ingredients.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers by placing in blender.
Mix all ingredients together in electric mixer.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° until done, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lazy-day cobbler
directions: Put the butter in a deep dish.
Place in oven to melt.

Beat together the 1 cup sugar, flour and milk. Beat to a smooth batter. Pour over the melted butter. Do not stir! Empty the fruit over the batter and sprinkle with 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: almond jello(diet)
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add sugar and boiling water. Wait a few seconds, then stir in milk and flavorings. Refrigerate until set.

title: pineapple-orange congealed salad
directions: Place pineapple on stove and bring to boil.
Remove from heat; add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in buttermilk, coconut, nuts and oranges.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch dish and chill.
This makes a large salad.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Rinse in cold water and drain well.
Add vegetables and Ranch dressing.
Mix and chill.

title: corn bread fish bake
directions: Thaw fish; cut fillets into 2 x 4-inch strips.
Set aside.
In large bowl, stir together corn meal and soda.
Add onion and peppers.
Beat together the buttermilk and eggs; stir into corn meal mixture, along with shortening.
Spread batter in greased 7 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place fish in rows atop batter.
Press into batter.
Stir together butter or oleo and mustard.
Spread over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: curry chicken
directions: Melt margarine; brown chicken and add tomato sauce.
Add curry, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over medium heat for 1 hour.
Very good over rice.

title: tv snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put cereals, pretzel sticks and nuts into roasting pans (or pan).
Melt butter in pan.
Blend in oil, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Sprinkle over dry ingredients; mix through.
Bake 1 1/2 hours; stir several times while baking.

title: chop suey pickles
directions: Slice very thin the cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Add enough cold water to cover vegetables and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add vinegar, mixed spices, water, sugar and celery salt and boil 10 minutes.
Add curry powder just before removing from stove.
Pack into bottles and seal.

title: mom's cooked custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour and enough milk to make paste in large saucepan.
Put rest of milk with rest of ingredients. Cook and stir constantly until thick and bubbly, then add vanilla.
Should be thick enough to have knife stand in it.

title: bologna salad
directions: Run bologna through food processor.
Mix in bowl with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve on a plate as a side dish or on bread as a sandwich.
Good!!

title: "crusty top" sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and measure; resift twice with soda.
Set aside. Cream butter and add sugar slowly, beating constantly to cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well. Stir in vanilla and turn batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
Place pan on rack to cool 5 minutes.
Loosen cake around edge of pan and edge of tube with dull side of knife.
Press toward pan rather than toward cake in order to protect crust.
Turn cake onto rack to cool completely.

title: potato buns
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in warm water.
Mix together with potatoes and sugar.
Let rise 1 hour.
Add shortening, eggs and salt.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour.
Knead.
Put in greased pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk or let rise overnight.
Shape into rolls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes until light brown.
Best served warm with homemade jam.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oil, margarine, eggs, and flavorings together. Add dry ingredients. Make into balls and dip in sugar. Press down, perhaps with a decorative drinking glass bottom. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until tinge of brown appears on edges.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook fryer, take off bone and skin.
Save broth.
Put remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir all together; add torn up chicken.
Leave nice size chunks.
Put in Pam sprayed pan or large size casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover the last 15 or 20 minutes to brown top of dressing.
Can make a day ahead and cover with Saran and refrigerate.
Then bake when ready to use.

title: roadside potatoes
directions: Take potatoes and put them in a 9x13 pan (sprayed with Pam). Heat milk or half and half, butter and salt.
Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake one hour at 325 degrees.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Work all together well.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Bake in oven at 375° to 400° until light brown.

title: dorene watts' gingersnaps
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients with liquids.
Let dough chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Roll balls in sugar before putting on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: creamy split pea soup
directions: Cook and stir kielbasa in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat about 5 minutes; drain.
Stir in soup, water and mustard.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in half and half, curry powder and pimentos; heat just until hot, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese if desired.

title: carrots with creme
directions: Put carrots, butter, salt, sugar and water in a saucepan. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until carrots are tender and water has almost evaporated, about 15 minutes.
Stir in cream and parsley.
Cook gently for about 2 minutes more, until cream is warm.
Serve hot.

title: norwegian christmas bread
directions: If possible, check temperature of warm water with thermometer. Sprinkle yeast over water in large warm bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add granulated sugar and salt.
Stir until well dissolved.
Add water, 3 eggs, 3 cups flour and cardamom.
Beat vigorously with wooden spoon or electric mixer at medium speed until smooth, about 3 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake medium to large baking potatoes.
Cut in half lengthwise. Scoop out and mix with all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 300° or until hot and cheese is melted.
Serves 10.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cooked cabbage in the bottom of a greased casserole dish. Combine soup, cheese and milk in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until pudding forms.
Let cool.
Add half and half and vanilla to pudding mixture.
Add 1 quart more of milk when ready to freeze.

title: country soup
directions: Place pork and salt pork in large soup pot.
Pour in 3 1/2 quarts water.
Bring to boil, then lower heat and simmer 1 hour. Add beans and whole onion.
Simmer 1 hour more.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix. Top with 3 oz. Chinese noodles. Bake at 325° in 1 1/2 quart casserole.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: In a large pot, melt the stick of butter and brown the onion (chopped).
Add 1 can tomatoes.
Slice the okra and add to the tomatoes and onion.
Add the second can of tomatoes along with a can of tomatoes along with one can of water.
Make sure that there is enough water to cover the okra.
Add the Lawry's along with the salt and pepper.
Simmer for awhile and keep adding water as it boils down.
Enjoy!

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Spray Pam in bottom of slow cooker or pot.
Add meat and kidney beans to cooker; chop cabbage in chunks. Add to pot, then add stewed tomatoes over cabbage.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is tender.
Mix together and season to taste. Serve with French bread or rolls.

title: bean and potato taco pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add milk and 1/4 cup taco seasoning mix.
Remove from heat and stir in potato flakes.
Press mixture on bottom and sides of two ungreased 10-inch pie plates.

title: merry christmas freeze
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into slightly greased mold.
Freeze.
Garnish with mint leaves and serve with holiday dinners.

title: sweet onion confetti
directions: Combine onions, bell pepper and pimento.
Set aside.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar, caraway seed and salt and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over onions.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Grease cookie sheet. Spread crescent rolls out and press onto cookie sheet, connecting the rolls. Bake 5 minutes as crescent roll directions indicate, until golden brown.
Cool.

title: low calorie fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Put remaining ingredients in a plastic bag with chicken pieces and shake.
Place on broiler rack and bake at 350° until browned (about 1 hour and 10 minutes).

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 20 minutes or a little longer at 350°.
Let cool.

title: sweet niblets("kiddie chow")
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in microwave.
Add the cereal.
Shake this mixture in a paper bag filled with one box of powdered sugar.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: In pan over medium heat, stir water and sugar until dissolved. Stir in nuts. Stir to coat until all liquid is gone. Cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
meat with onion and pepper.
Add salt and pepper, chili powder and garlic salt to taste.
Line cake pan
or casserole
dish
with tortillas.
Then add a layer of hamburger, 2
cans beans and then sprinkle a layer of cheese. Repeat
layers. Top
with	cream
of
chicken
soup
and then Ro-Tel.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: bubbling pineapple punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice and apricot nectar in a large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.
Makes 25 to 30 servings.

title: ham, broccoli and spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine cheese and milk; mix well.
Toss spaghetti with margarine.
Combine 1 cup ham and all other ingredients.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Spread remaining 1 cup ham on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6 people.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Mash both cans of refried beans in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ground beef over beans.
Spread cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve with chips and toppings to individual taste.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
May be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Mix Crisco and half of sugar.
Beat rest of ingredients until peaked.
Mix together.

title: banana bread
directions: Place cream cheese and eggs in bowl and blend with electric mixer on low for 2 minutes.
Place bananas in small bowl and mash with a fork.
Add bananas to cream cheese and eggs and blend with mixer for 1 minute.
Add cake mix and mix until the ingredients are blended together.
Grease 2 loaf pans with shortening.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: harvest apple pie
directions: Fill pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan with apples.
Combine next 6 ingredients and pour over apples.
Cover with top crust and bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over crust.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until topping is bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: treebeards red beans
directions: Wash beans under cold, running water.
Place in a heavy 5 quart pot.
Cover with 2 quarts water.
Let beans soak overnight. Or, cover beans with 2 quarts water, bring to a boil.
reduce heat, cover and boil 2 minutes.
Turn off heat and let sit 1 hour before continuing.
Do not drain off water.
Two hours before serving, add chopped onions, celery and bell pepper to beans. With spoon, gently push vegetables below water line.
Cover pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy chili mac dish
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix beef and macaroni, chili and tomato soups and mix well in skillet. Cook through and add cheese on top to melt.
May add onions and green pepper when browning beef.

title: stir-fry
directions: Cut everything into bite size slices.
Fry the pieces of chicken in a little oil and seasoning.
When chicken is completely done, add the bite sized vegetables and saute about 10 minutes. Can be served as is or with sweet and sour sauce.
Also you can add a cup or two of cooked rice to stretch recipe.

title: aunt lula's pregnant pickles
directions: Place onions in bottom of 1 gallon jar.
Top with cucumber slices.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers. Cover jar and refrigerate for 1 week before serving.
The pickles keep 9 months.

title: grace iced tea
directions: Add water to make 1 gallon.
Serve over ice.

title: yellow cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter and add well-beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add flour, milk and baking powder, a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and bake at 350°.
Very good with caramel filling or chocolate.

title: sweet-and-sour chicken
directions: Cut boneless chicken in chunks or strips; cook a few minutes until almost done.
Dip into egg and roll in flour.
Fry in frying pan. Repeat process.
When all chicken is fried, place in pot. Cut up green peppers, onions and garlic.
Saut in frying pan until caramelized. Add vegetables to chicken; add pineapple chunks, water, sweet-sour sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook until it starts to boil.
Enjoy!

title: east side house dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, vinegar last.
Beat for 4 minutes with electric beater.
Makes one quart of dressing. Refrigerate and use as needed.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins. Cool.
Peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup margarine, stirring occasionally, until almost melted.

Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Fold in potatoes and turn into greased 2-quart casserole. Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through. Serves 8.

title: vegetable garden casserole
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons of oil; stir in garlic and bread crumbs.
Remove pan from heat; stir in 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Spread onion mixture in bottom of casserole dish. Layer zucchini and squash, alternating them, then a layer of tomatoes; sprinkle with Mozzarella and basil.
Repeat layering and drizzle remaining oil over vegetables.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake for 20 minutes; uncover and bake for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender at 350°.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Boil for 5 minutes or until small amount of mixture forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water. Gradually beat into stiffly beaten egg whites. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixture holds its shape.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased pan or waxed paper.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Peel and slice the apples. Pack into quart jars. Mix together the sugar, water, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and lemon juice. Cook until just begins to slightly thicken. Pour over apples in jars. Cook in water bath for 20 minutes. Yield: 7 to 8 quarts.

title: boston fruit cookies
directions: Cover 1/2 box raisins with water and cook 5 minutes until plumped.
Cool raisins.
Save hot juice (1 cup).
Add ingredients in order.
Add nuts, chips, cherries, coconut or other additions of your choice (i.e., peanut butter chips, other "candied" fruit, nuts, etc.).
Bake by teaspoon at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and milk in double boiler.
Mix together oleo, sugar, flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Put 1/2 the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan (don't pat down).
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Add 1 (12 ounce) package chocolate chips and walnuts (chopped).
Pour caramel mix on top, then sprinkle rest of dough on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well; add dry ingredients and spices. Mix thoroughly.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Divide mixture among 3 one pound coffee cans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Makes 3 small loaves.
Good served warm or with cream cheese.
Better made a day or 2 ahead.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Melt Velveeta, soup and tomatoes. Stir in diced chicken. Rotate layers of crushed Doritos and chicken mixture in oblong baking dish, ending with chicken mixture. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: egg bake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Separate muffins and lay in pan.
Mix onion, eggs and milk; pour over muffins.
Layer cheeses, then sausage, then cheeses.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: caramels
directions: Sprinkle nuts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, syrup, butter, 1 carton cream in heavy pan. Bring to boil.
When it starts to boil, add rest of cream.
Cook to 245° to 248°.
Pour over nuts. Cut when cool, wrap in wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package instructions; drain well. Mix mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Fold in broccoli.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with crushed crackers and then melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: florida punch
directions: Combine and dissolve sugar and water together.
Add fruit juices and undiluted lemonade.
Freeze.
Add the ginger ale when ready to serve.
(Serves 100.)

title: so-easy chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven.
Reserve 1/3 cup frosting.
In large bowl, combine remaining frosting, peanut butter and egg; blend well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
By hand, stir in flour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on a lightly greased cookie pan.
Flatten each 2-inches thick with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Lightly frost with reserved 1/3 cup frosting.
Yield: 48 cookies.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put in a large bowl.
In the winter months I use Schwan's frozen fruit mix.
I slightly unthaw and cut smaller.
I like to slice kiwi fruit over the top.
Also cut one into salad.

title: caramel icing
directions: After melting butter, add brown sugar, vanilla and cream. Boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Beat until cool enough to spread onto cake.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips and shortening over low heat.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Mix in peanuts.
Spoon into 1-inch size muffin cups or drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper covered cookie sheet.
Cool until set; store tightly covered.
Makes about 48.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook fresh carrots until done and let cool. Mix all other ingredients together and add carrots. Marinate overnight.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: applebaum's italiano salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Marinate 24 hours. Stir occasionally while marinating.
This salad takes about 1 hour to prepare and keeps 1 week.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli, bacon, Cheddar cheese and raisins in a bowl.
Mix together the last 3 ingredients and pour over the salad. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream together sugar and oleo. Add eggs, well beaten. Sift together flour, soda, salt, and cinnamon and add to mixture. Bake in oblong pan for 45 minutes at 350.

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pie plate.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in sugar and butter.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to egg mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Spread batter into prepared pie plate.
Bake 35 minutes or until set (pie will not test done in center).
Cool completely.
Cut into wedges. Serve with ice cream.
Top with your favorite Hershey's Chocolate Shoppe topping.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into small bars or balls.
Place on a cookie sheet, covered with waxed paper.
Chill 20 minutes.

title: butter biscuits
directions: Grate butter/margarine into flour and mix well - I like to use my hands.
Add buttermilk mix with spoon.
Roll out on flour wax paper.
Cut with biscuit cutter or a glass.
Put on pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water until raisins are plump.
Drain liquid into cup; add water to liquid to equal 1/2 cup.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Blend flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir well.
Add rolled oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop full teaspoons of dough 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Rinse beans and drain.
Add green pepper and onions.
Mix together sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over beans. Add sugar, if needed.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, layer 12 of the ice cream sandwiches, cutting to fit if necessary. Spread layer of Cool Whip. Drizzle chocolate syrup over Cool Whip. Sprinkle with Heath bits.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Cook in hot shortening over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: mushroom-rice bake
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine water, uncooked rice and 1 teaspoon salt; bring to boiling.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet and bake about 12 to 15 minutes. Take out as edges brown and tops are light brown.
Cool slightly and remove to wire cooling rack.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chop into little pieces. Put 1 package of taco seasoning in the hamburger.
Add one cup of water and let simmer. Simmer until all water is gone.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all ingredients except crackers.
Put in a greased baking dish.
Put crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly and light brown. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nanah's perfect pralines
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, combine sugar and buttermilk with soda.
Boil, stirring constantly, until it holds together between your fingers when tested in cold water, about 6 or 7 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Each praline should have 4 to 5 pecans.
Let cool until firm.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: really good salad dressing
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a blender.
Add the last 4 ingredients and mix just until blended.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick; add butter and mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla and almond extract.
Chill overnight.
Dough must be ice cold to roll.
Roll thin and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool, then frost, if desired.
Makes 8 to 12 dozen.

title: carrot marinade
directions: Cook carrots; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients to make sauce.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate.
When ready, lift carrots from sauce and serve.
This keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook vegetable noodles in salted water.
Drain.
Put noodles, Italian dressing, chopped tomato, chopped bell pepper, onion, cucumber and grated cheese in bowl and mix together. Sprinkle dill weed, garlic powder and parsley flakes over salad.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough flour to make dough stiff. Roll out quite thick.
Cut with a large cutter.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: sour bean soup
directions: Boil ham with the onion for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove ham (do not discard broth).
Cut into small pieces.
Add water to broth to suit taste.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook until done.
Add beans and cut up ham; heat to boiling and thicken.
If desired to make "sour" add vinegar to taste.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into 2 well-greased pie plates. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes its own crust.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly margarine, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and sugar.
Shape into balls.
Refrigerate overnight. In double boiler, melt chocolate chips with paraffin.
Keep over hot water while working.
(Be careful not to let water boil over into chocolate.)
Using tongs, dip balls, one at a time, into chocolate.
Cool on wax paper.
Refrigerate in container indefinitely.

title: portofino mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple, cranberry sauce and juice.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly. Fold in pecans and turn into a two-quart mold or flat casserole. Chill until firm.
Beat the softened cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sour cream until mixture is smooth.
Spread over gelatin.
Chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and add milk and shortening.
Sift remaining ingredients together; add to egg mixture and beat well.
Pour into hot, greased 8-inch cast-iron skillet and bake in hot oven (400°) until it shrinks from the sides of the skillet, about 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini. Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Make a well in the center; add zucchini mixture and blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake 40 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: beef and cabbage dish
directions: Shred cabbage.
Spread 1/2 cabbage in a baking dish.
Brown ground beef, pepper and onion in skillet.
Put 1/2 the mixture over the cabbage.
Add rest of the cabbage and top with meat.
Spread tomato soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious.

title: curried cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Split muffins and toast.
Spread filling on muffins; broil until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan. Cut up onion and simmer until tender. Add drained sauerkraut and mushrooms. Cover and simmer for 20 min. Add mushroom soup (do not dilute). Add mixture to cooked noodles and mix well. Bake at 350 for 20 to 30 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vivian's dump cake
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients.
Pour margarine over all.
Sprinkle coconut and walnuts on top and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Mix deviled ham, onion, pepper, salt, Italian seasoning and bread crumbs.
Stuff into pockets of chicken breasts.
Toothpick closed, if necessary.
Arrange in baking dish.
Melt butter and stir in salad dressing mix.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (or grill outdoors, basting occasionally).

title: white sauce
directions: Double the recipe to make 1 gallon.
Whip with whisk until smooth.
Let set overnight.

title: jalapeno corn bread(bread machine)
directions: Measure carefully, placing all ingredients in bread machine pan in order given.
Select Basic/White cycle.
Use medium or light crust color.
Do Not use Delayed Cycle.
Remove baked bread from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 1/2 pound loaf.

title: egg casserole for brunch
directions: Scramble eggs dry.
Melt together soup, sherry, mushrooms, green pepper, margarine and milk.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350 until golden brown.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Brown hamburger. Add onion if desired. Do not drain. Stir in flour until absorbed. Add milk and stir until thickened. Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: white bread plus
directions: In a large mixer bowl, mix together 3 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, water and shortening.
Shortening need not be melted.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add egg and 1 cup flour.
Beat 1/2 minute at low speed.
Then at high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 cups of flour until mixture starts to roll away from side of bowl. Turn out to lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Return to large clean oiled bowl and let rise approximately 1 hour, covered.
Should double in size. Punch down and make bread pan size loaves and place in greased bread pans, let rise 1 hour or doubled.

title: homemade ice cream for 5 qt freezer(no egg ice cream)
directions: Use an electric mixer to mix the canned milks, whipping cream, vanilla, and sugar together to get the sugar mixed smooth before pouring into your freezer. Finish filling the freezer with milk, pack the tank with ice and salt according to the manufactures instructions and freeze.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions together; salt and pepper to taste.
Add flour to thicken.
When slightly browned, add can of Veg-All.
Pour into casserole dish.
Separate biscuits and cover top of mixture.
Sprinkle celery salt on biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.
Serves 4 to 6.
(I like to put slices of American cheese on top of casserole, before I add biscuits.)

title: anise cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter. Add sugar gradually and blend well.
Stir in unbeaten egg yolks and anise extract until batter is smooth.
Add flour mixture.
Nip off little pieces of dough and roll into balls size of a cherry. Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Beat egg and sugar. Add flour, salt, apples and nuts. Grease and flour 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Reserve 1 quart of broth.
Take rest of broth (add water if necessary) and cook noodles for 10 minutes.
Strain and add to chicken.

title: manhattan salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot water.
Add vinegar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Pour a thin layer into mold and chill until firm. Chill remaining jello until slightly thickened.
Combine apples, celery, nuts and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and fold into slightly thickened jello.
Pour into mold over firm layer.
When jello is completely firm, take out of mold and serve on top of lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: german fruit salad
directions: Drain and reserve juice from fruit.
Mix together first four ingredients.
Add enough fruit juice to make mixture about the consistency of whipping cream.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Mix creamy mixture and drained fruit. Fold in Dream Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: special k bars
directions: Combine the syrup and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring it to a boil and remove it from the heat.
Add peanut butter and cereal. Spread this in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let it set.
Melt the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together and spread them over the bars.

title: dilled potato soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion; cook 4 to 6 minutes or until soft.
Add potatoes and 2 cups cold water; bring to boil.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: "great" chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil. Boil to soft ball stage (232°).
Add vanilla, butter and chocolate.
Beat with spoon until candy loses its gloss.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a thin layer on a platter. Put on a layer of salsa, then sliced jalapeno pepper.
Add green pepper, onions and tomatoes.
Add about 3/4 of can of black olives. Top with both cheeses.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook ground chuck, onions and garlic in a skillet until brown. Add soup and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cook slowly until cheese melts.
Stir in bread crumbs. Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Cook in boiling water with salt until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place peppers on baking sheet.
Stuff with meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook broth, onions, celery and potatoes until tender. Add Veg-All and soup. Mix well. Add Velveeta cheese and let melt.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and make into walnut size balls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and toasted white bread.
Mix in the onions, celery, eggs, poultry seasoning and sage.
You may use mushroom soup, if so desired.
Mix mixture with your broth from your turkey.
Add water or a can of broth to make mixture smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: lemon banana salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 7-Up.
Add sliced bananas and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix pecans, flour and butter.
Press into 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix chocolate pudding according to directions.
In separate bowl, mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and approximately 1 cup Cool Whip.
Let crust cool completely.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Then spread pudding over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Chill in refrigerator for about 1 hour before serving.

title: health bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Simmer raisins in the hot water for 5 minutes; cool.
Mix dry ingredients, then add the sour milk, which has been mixed with soda and molasses.
Add the egg, nuts and cooked raisins with their water and stir until blended.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° or until set.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Put crackers on top.
Pour on juice, then melted margarine.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients and stir together.
Place in baking dish.
Place baking dish in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken noodle parmesan
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add noodles and chicken over low heat.
Heat through; stir occasionally.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring to boil 1 cup orange soda.
Remove from heat.
Add orange jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold soda.
Let sit in refrigerator for 1 hour or more, until just set.
Whip 1 package Dream Whip or small Cool Whip.
Blend together the set jello and Cool Whip.
Add small can of Mandarin oranges.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Blanche cabbage 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients except carrot and onion sauteed in chicken broth.
Stuff inside 2 cabbage leaves.
Secure with toothpicks.
Spoon sauteed carrot and onion over top of cabbage rolls.
Cook 40 minutes at 350° in glass dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together corn, eggs, milk and butter.
Then add corn muffin mix.
Blend ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish, greased with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Should be somewhat firm.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils; boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 cup.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil the oleo, water and cocoa.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, mixed with sour cream and soda.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cornish hens delight
directions: Salt and pepper hens.
Brown hens with onion and butter for 10 minutes.
Add broth and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove hens.
Add cornstarch to drippings.
Stir constantly until smooth.
Blend in soup and sour cream.
Place hen in baking dish.
Pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients well and use to barbecue just about anything from ribs to hamburgers.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and cut stem of okra (not too short).
Pack in jars. Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in saucepan.
Pour over okra while hot and seal.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Sift
1 cup powdered sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa together.
Add well
beaten
egg
yolks.
Beat
whites until stiff. Fold in first
mixture.
Bake
35 minutes at 325° in long pan (baking sheet),
greased
slightly
and floured.
Turn out on dish towel. Let
cool.
Spread
with
whipped cream which has been sweetened to
taste.
Add
vanilla to this mixture also. Roll and ice
with 1
or
1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa,
vanilla and
enough cream to make it spreading consistency.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Cook meat and onions in olive oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid; add water to make 1 cup.
Add mushrooms and 1 cup liquid to meat and onions.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Place in baking dish.
Arrange potatoes over meat. Mix the soup, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour.
Sprinkle with crumbs, if desired; bake another 30 minutes.
(I put this into two casseroles and freeze one.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and egg. Mix together sugars.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Add butterscotch chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve or refrigerate.

title: hamburger and baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Stir in ground beef and brown.
Add pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, dry mustard, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix and pour into casserole or baking dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2-qt casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: best pinto beans ever
directions: Rinse beans. Cover with water and boil for 15 minutes. Then start over with fresh water and let come to a boil. Saute onions and garlic until wilted and add to beans. Cook for 1 hour and 45 minutes on medium heat. Add salt and pepper. Add Tabasco sauce and bacon and cook 15 minutes or until done.

title: hearty salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking pan.
Place fish on bed of onions in prepared pan.
Combine mushrooms, tomatoes, green pepper and parsley.
Spread mixture over fish.
Combine wine, lemon juice, salt and pepper; pour over vegetables and fish. Cover pan with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until fish flakes easily.
Serve with lemon slices.

title: deer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Roll into 8 rolls.
Be sure to pack and roll firmly.
Place on broiler pan. Bake in low oven (150°) for 8 hours.

title: lemon icebox pie(weight watchers)
directions: Blend pudding with milk.
Add Crystal Lite.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine sugar and water and bring to a boil. Add cornstarch to boiling sugar water mixture. Boil until clear. Remove from stove. Add butter, the beaten egg yolks, vinegar, salt and vanilla. Stir well and pour into pie shell. Bake 20 minutes at 300°. Remove from oven. Beat 3 egg whites until stiff, add sugar gradually. Spread meringue over Pie. Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and make a well in center of large bowl. Add liquids; mix well.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 to 4 loaves.

title: tuna cornbread pie
directions: Lay lemon slices in the bottom of a lightly greased 10-inch pie plate.
Drain the flaked tuna and blend well with bread crumbs, onion, eggs and soup.
Gently turn tuna mix over lemon slices. Heat oven to 400°.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Put pineapple in strainer and let drain.
Prepare two (9 x 5) loaf pans.
Grease well and flour.
In a bowl, combine first 5 dry ingredients.
Add nuts; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Blend well. Fold in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until just blended.
Spoon batter into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool in pans on rack 10 minutes. Remove from pans; cool on rack completely.
Makes 2 loaves; 36 slices each with 162 calories.

title: corn patch casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons fat.
Combine tomatoes and corn.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch and season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and a little pepper.
Put in casserole and cover with 1 cup grated cheese.
Cook in slow oven at 350° at 30 minutes.

title: feather lite rolls
directions: Add shortening to milk while milk is still warm.
When milk has cooled, dissolve yeast in water and add to milk.
Add sugar and salt, eggs and flour, beat well.
Let rise in bowl for 20 minutes. Knead dough for 2 minutes.

title: easy caramel popcorn
directions: In a large, shallow pan, combine popcorn and nuts.
Place in a 250° oven while preparing glaze.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over warm popcorn and nuts to coat well.
Bake.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Bring butter, sugar, milk and marshmallows to boil; take off heat.
Add chocolate chips, shaved Hershey milk chocolate bar and nuts.
Stir until all is completely melted.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan or greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm enough to cut.

title: party punch
directions: Fill to 1 gallon with water.
Serves 20.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and onions in crock-pot.
Blend sour cream, soup and margarine in a bowl.
Add to potatoes; cook on high 3 to 4 hours.
May prepare with cooked potatoes.
Cook on low for 1 hour. Yield:
15 servings.

title: goolosh
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Boil noodles until tender and drain.
Layer noodles, sauce, meat, and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put moistened rice in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Place chicken in next.
Combine cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water, then pour over chicken.
Add salt and pepper. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread boys cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then mix all ingredients together. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out gingerbread boys.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in preheated 375° oven.
Trim with icing.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain and set aside.
Brown meat and drain; then add macaroni, tomatoes, salt and water.
Cook together for 30 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir.
Add cheese (do not stir).
Cool 10 minutes, covered, until melted. Serves 6.

title: raspberry slush
directions: Combine pineapple juice, lemonade, lemon juice, punch mix, sugar and raspberries.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons of fruit mixture.
Freeze in a large plastic container for 12 hours. Thaw slightly; put in punch bowl and top with lemon-lime soda.

title: tasty salmonettes
directions: Drain juice from salmon; set aside.
Put salmon in mixing bowl and stir in the egg.
When it is gummy, add 1/2 cup flour.
Stir thoroughly.
Mixture will be thick.
Do not add any salt; pepper is okay.

title: marinated vegetable medley
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil and salt and pepper in a saucepan. Stir and heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Mix all vegetables together.

title: homemade deep dish pizza
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet with 1 clove garlic and fresh onion. Mix in tomato sauce, whole tomatoes and spaghetti mix, then add salt, pepper, sage, chili powder, cumin, parsley, oregano and basil.
Heat on low with a lid on pan.
Mix your basic white bread dough recipe.
Rub olive oil on bottom of pizza pan; put dough rolled out on pizza pan.
Rub olive oil on dough.
Put sauce on top of dough, then top it with your cheeses and other toppings.
Makes 1 large pizza.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add cocoa, milk, allspice, cloves, cinnamon, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Blend flour, stirring well.
When it starts to get hard to stir with spoon, wash hands thoroughly.
Do not over flour.
Wash hands; get a piece of dough and roll in hand.
If it doesn't stick to hand, it is ready.
If sticky, add more flour.
Spoon dough on an ungreased cookie sheet and roll in hand about 1-inch round, then flatten on sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Ice when cool.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Divide cheese equally into 3 parts.
Cook macaroni and drain. Layer 1/3 of macaroni in lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat again.
Top with remaining macaroni (reserve remaining cheese).
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash and core 4 medium apples.
Fill cavity 1/2 full with raisins.
Pack the rest with brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Dot top with margarine.
Place in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Turn after 4 minutes.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Crush up Butterfingers into pieces. Mix up Butterfingers with Cool Whip. Put into a graham cracker crust and freeze for a couple of hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Do in layers:
Corn chips, Mozzarella cheese, black olives, green olives and onion.
Repeat first five and a thin layer of nacho cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted. Add lettuce, tomatoes and salsa.
Sizes are up to you.

title: final exam brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Mix sugar, melted butter and chocolate in large bowl.
Beat in eggs and mix in flour and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan, greased.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: "black eyed peas"
directions: Cook bacon (do not cook until crisp).
Drain grease.
In pan, combine bacon, onions, butter and black-eyed peas juice.
Simmer until onions are done.
Add peas, mix and heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with almond slices (optional).
Serve with Triscuits or other crackers.

title: lemon zucchini soup
directions: In heavy saucepan or Dutch oven, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until soft, but not browned, 6 minutes.
Add the zucchini slices, cover and cook until soft, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir to keep from browning.

title: sauerkraut and pork chops
directions: Put sauerkraut, apple, potato and caraway seed in pot with pork chops.
Cover with water.
Cook until pork chops are tender.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Chop broccoli and cook as directed. Add water and chicken base, then add velveeta in chunks.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
In separate pan cook noodles. Add milk, broccoli and noodles to cheese mixture.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: pudding salad
directions: Cook until thickens, then chill about 1 1/2 or 2 hours.
Add 1 can orange segments and 1 large tub Cool Whip.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Heat soup.
Cream the cheese and add with gelatin to hot soup; cool.
Add vegetables and mayonnaise.
Place sliced stuffed olives in bottom of mold and pour salad mixture over olives.
When set, turn out on lettuce to serve.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Place boneless chicken breasts in dish.
Cover with sliced cheese.
Thin the
cream of chicken soup with white wine and spoon over chicken.
Spread stuffing over soup and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Saute turkey bacon, ground beef and onion; put in crock-pot. Add all other ingredients.
Cook until heated to own satisfaction.

title: fool-proof pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Mix egg, water and vinegar.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients and mix well. Pat into 5 rounds and flatten slightly.
Chill between sheets of plastic at least 20 minutes.

title: creamy fruit and cake delight
directions: Divide cake cubes and fruit evenly among 6 dessert glasses, reserving several strawberry slices for garnish, if desired.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir whipped topping into gelatin with wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened. Spoon into dessert glasses.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm. Garnish with reserved strawberry slices.

title: broccoli muffins
directions: Mix ingredients well and let stand 3 to 4 minutes before pouring in pan.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In small bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla.
With wooden spoon, beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon (rounded) onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Beat oil, lemon juice, salt, mustard and cayenne pepper until creamy in appearance.
Pour over cauliflower, mushrooms, peas, onion and bacon.
Will keep up to 10 days in the refrigerator.

title: finger salad
directions: Lay out rolls flat.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Cool completely. Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread on the cooled rolls.
Layer the vegetables on top, then top with cheese. Press into mixture.
Cool at least 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Prepare fried noodles.
Remove skin and bones from chicken and discard.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Blend 1/2 tablespoon each of the sherry and soy sauce and 1 teaspoon of the cornstarch in large bowl. Mix in chicken.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix biscuit dough and roll out to a rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread the sausage over the rectangle, roll up about the size of a rolling pin.
Wrap in aluminum foil and store in the refrigerator or freezer.
If frozen, take out a few minutes before cutting, but it must be chilled good to cut easily.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices, place on cookie sheet and bake until nicely brown.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine flour (do not sift), sugar and beer.
Mix well with spoon or hands.
Spray pan with cooking spray and put mixture in there.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: savory spinach artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Spoon into 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with assorted Nabisco crackers.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add beaten egg, molasses, then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
The batter is soft but makes fine cake. Bake in greased shallow pan.

title: chicken-chip casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: micro party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until cereal is hot. Stir occasionally during cooking.
Place in an airtight container.
Store in a cool place or freezer.
Recipe Yield:
About 10 cups party mix.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute vegetables in large pot with 1/4 cup water until vegetables are soft, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Add one can of tomato juice and two cups water.
Add salt to taste.
Cover and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut Velveeta up in chunks.
Pour Ro-Tel over top.
Microwave on Medium power for 3 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Very good with nacho chips over vegetables, fresh or cooked.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and blend.
Add broth slowly to avoid lumps, then milk.
Return to heat and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Season well with salt.
Add onion, olives, cooked spaghetti, chicken, mushrooms and 1/2 almonds.
Mix well and turn into a greased 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine melted margarine, bread crumbs and cheese. Sprinkle over spaghetti mixture along with remaining almonds. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick and easy strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar, corn syrup and cornstarch in saucepan. Heat over medium flame until boiling, stirring constantly.
After boiling for a couple minutes, remove from heat and stir in Jell-O. Pour small amount of Jell-O mixture on bottom of prepared pie crust.
Arrange strawberries in crust and spoon Jell-O mixture over berries.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle raw rice over bottom of pan.
Heat the 2 cans of soup with milk and blend.
Pour over rice.
Place pieces of chicken over the top and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal pan with foil and bake at 325° for at least 2 hours or until done.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together. Mix all ingredients together. Put in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Delicious served warm with Breyers vanilla ice cream!

title: marie's hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Saute onion and green pepper; add to hamburger.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place hamburger mixture in a greased casserole.
Layer creamed corn on this.
Add the mashed potatoes as the last layer.
Top with grated cheese if desired.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: no fail pie crust(makes at least 5 pie crusts.)
directions: Break egg in measuring cup, add vinegar and stir.
Fill cup with water, add to flour mixture.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry cutter until pea size.
Sprinkle water on dough, one tablespoon at a time.
Lightly mix with a fork.
Round into ball; cut in half for two.
