Makes 1 (8 or 9-inch) double crust pie or two single shells. Bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Watch carefully.

title: fruity bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Mix until all bread lumps are gone.
Add sugar and raisins.
Mix well to combine.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish. Bake 25 minutes or until set.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple crunch
directions: Slice apples and place in casserole.
Stir granulated sugar into sliced apples.
Combine remaining ingredients and put over apples.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange sponge
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water, 5 minutes.
Heat remaining 3/4 cup water, add grated rinds and simmer 10 minutes. Add to gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and fruit juices and chill until thickened.
Fold in egg whites, turn into individual molds and chill until firm.
Unmold.
Yields 6 portions.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat egg, add sugar and shortening; mix well.
Add flour and yeast, stir
until well blended.
Put in bowl and cover.
Keep in refrigerator.
You don't have to let rise before baking.
Put large spoonfuls in greased muffin pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This will keep in the refrigerator for 1 week.
This will make about 15 large muffins.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(the pie that does the impossible by making it's own crust.)
directions: 350°; -9 or 10-inch pie pan.

title: soup burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, egg and bread crumbs.
Shape into four patties and brown on both sides.
Pour condensed soup over burgers and simmer 20 minutes.
Top with canned French fried onions.

title: ham salad stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix together the ham, celery, pecans, olives and onion in a large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Place stem end of tomatoes down on cutting board.
Cut each tomato about 2/3 way down into 8 equal wedges.
Open to allow space for stuffing. Place each tomato on a lettuce leaf lined salad plate and stuff with equal amounts of ham salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crock-pot tortilla stack
directions: Crumble 1/4 of ground beef into bottom of slow cooker.
Top with 1/4 of tortilla wedges.
In small bowl, combine soup and taco mix.
Spread 1/4 of soup mixture over tortillas in pot.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of tomatoes.
Repeat, layering until all ingredients are in pot.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with remaining ingredients, as desired.
Makes 6 or 7 servings.

title: french quarter green beans
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions; drain.
Melt margarine in Dutch oven; add soup and cream cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cream cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in green beans, onion flakes, water chestnuts, garlic salt, pepper and Cheddar cheese. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2 quart casserole.
Top with almonds; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter and mix in sugar.
Drain pineapple and place in skillet.
Mix cake mix and pour in skillet. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir well.
Put in pizza pan. Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven, remove and cool.
Also, can use a 9 x 15-inch cookie pan.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar. Spread over baked crust.
Put fresh fruit on top of cream cheese. Glaze with cornstarch and lemon juice.
Makes 24 slices.

title: baked squirrel
directions: Panboil squirrels for 30 to 40 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix soup per instructions and add onions.
Position squirrel in casserole.
Add spices to taste.
Add soup and onion mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting at least twice.
Serve with noodles. Serves 3 to 4. Preparation Time:
2 1/2 hours.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Cream the cheese with sugar and mayonnaise.
Add drained pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream topping.
Freeze.
Take out 45 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger-barley soup
directions: In a large pot, brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add all ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
May be frozen.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: clam and spinach pasta
directions: Chop garlic, shallots and onion, sauteed in olive oil about 5 minutes.
Defrost spinach (can be done in microwave).
Drain spinach in a strainer and saute with the garlic, etc.
Chop tomatoes and toss in with mixture being sauteed.
About 5 minutes before serving, add clams and clam juice.
Serve over your choice of pasta.
A little red pepper is a nice addition if you like it spicy and hot.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese, syrup and lemon juice until creamy.
Fold in fruit, marshmallows and whipping cream.
Pour into 6 cup ring mold.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with assorted fruit and serve with cinnamon stick.

title: baked new potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Place half of sliced potatoes in a shallow greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle salt and pepper, 1/2 cup cheese, half of bacon and half of butter and onion.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in pie shell.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer or until filling is firm.

title: tomato and zucchini casserole
directions: Melt margarine and garlic salt; saute bread crumbs.
Place layer of tomatoes sprinkled with salt and brown sugar.
Layer in order:
onions, zucchini, bread crumbs and cheese.
Repeat.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate, nuts and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Mix eggs and milk together.
Brown sausage and drain.
Place 1/2 cheese in bottom of each pie shell.
Cover with 1/2 sausage in each shell.
Top with beaten eggs and milk, divided evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes, do not peel but slice French fry style and boil in salted water.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Season with onion and garlic to taste.
Add 1 can mushroom soup and milk. Layer potatoes and meat mixture in a large casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pudding cheesecake in 15 minutes(choose tart-sweet lemon or luscious pineapple cream flavor)
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup of milk until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly with eggbeater 1 minute (do not overbeat).

title: jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip meat.
Let set covered overnight. Dry on racks in oven on low heat at 200° to 250°.
Turn as needed, 3 to 3 1/2 hours, or can be dried in an electric smoker.

title: party pie
directions: Break the ladyfingers in half and place in pie dish to form the crust. Combine condensed milk and lemon juice. Add pineapple, marshmallows, 1/2 of the whipped cream and 1/2 of the cherries. Place the filling in the crust of ladyfingers and top with the remaining cream. Decorate with the remaining cherries. Enjoy!

title: punch
directions: Mix in large pot marked for 2 gallons.
Add water to fill. Put in jug and freeze.
Use strawberry or cherry for red, lemon for yellow or lime for green.

title: baked cheddar olives
directions: In a bowl, combine cheese and oleo; add flour and cayenne. Blend until combined well.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper and wrap or mold each tablespoon around each of the olives completely.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes or until pastry is golden.
Serve warm.

title: christmas jam
directions: Cook cranberries and apples in water until tender.
Add pineapple, sugar and lemon.
Boil until thick and clear.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine margarine, milk and egg.
Beat well.
Add pumpkin and beat smooth.
Stir biscuit mix and spice together.
Add to the batter and stir until lumpy.
Spray 12 muffin cups with cooking spray.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each muffin cup.
Sprinkle evenly with sugar substitute, if desired.
Cover with remaining batter.
(Without sweetener, simply spoon the batter into the muffin cups.)
Bake in preheated 425° oven about 15 minutes.
Don't overbake!
Makes 12 muffins.

title: tonya's fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl; stir in sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir together with butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts if preferred.
Pour into prepared pie pan.
Bake for 30 minutes or until set.
Cool and serve with ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
MMMMMMM Good!

title: lemon chicken
directions: Heat butter in 10-inch skillet until melted.
Cook chicken in butter
over medium heat (about 10 minutes).
Add wine and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place lemon slices on chicken.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
Heat wine mixture to boil.
Cook 3 minutes or until reduced to about half. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Makes 4 servings; 190 calories, 9g fat.

title: may basket cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and molasses; then add egg yolk.
Mix well.
Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
Sift into creamed mixture and mix well.
Wrap dough in foil and chill. Roll a small portion of the dough at a time to 1/8-inch thick. Keep remaining dough chilled until ready to roll out.
Cut out cookies with round or flower-shaped cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Decorate with cake decorator and frosting or with frosting in a pressure can.
Makes about 6 dozen small cookies.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Mix everything together and pour into deep dish pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle(about 1 pound)
directions: Put sugar, molasses and water in saucepan and heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Boil, without stirring, until syrup reaches hard-crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat and add butter or margarine and baking soda; stir just enough to mix well.
Stir in chopped peanuts.

title: cream cheese cake squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar for 5 minutes, then pour over crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over the top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 18.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler. Make a thickening of cornstarch in a small amount of water. Beat eggs with Worcestershire. Add cornstarch, eggs, beer and mustard to melted cheese. Beat with rotary beater or electric mixer frequently until smooth and thickened. Add red pepper to taste. Serve over saltine crackers. Top with chopped onions which have marinated in cider vinegar, if desired.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add 1/2 stick of margarine and cheese.
Put in buttered dish.
Crush crackers.
Mix with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, mix for about 2 minutes. Pour into two wax paper lined 9 inch layer pans.
Bake for 30 - 35 minutes at 350 degrees.
May also use a 9 inch x 13 inch pan. Frost with your favorite icing.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 70 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken enchiladas(imuy delicioso!)
directions: Fry tortillas in oil for 10 seconds each, then set aside on a plate.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together in a bowl.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful of mixture on each tortilla, roll up and place in oblong casserole (with Pam sprayed on bottom).
After putting in all 12 tortillas, pour remaining sauce on top.
Cook 25 minutes; sprinkle cheese on top and cook until melted.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve with chopped lettuce, salsa and rice.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: Chop bacon and start to fry.
When partially done, add finely chopped onion.
When onion starts to brown, pour off grease.
Add beans, brown sugar and ketchup.
Stir well.
Cover pan; simmer slowly for 5 minutes.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 300° (stir once).

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order in shallow dish.
Serve cold with nacho chips.

title: cranberry sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, butter, eggs, sweet potatoes and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Fold in chopped berries and nuts.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soup, bouillon cubes, water, pepper, margarine and dried vegetable soup mix.
Bring to a boil.
Next, butter casserole dish, and pour in mixture, then add rice, stir and cover.
Cook for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: regina's olive garden salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onions, tomatoes, olives and peppers.
When time to serve, pour croutons on top with dressing.
Toss and serve.

title: amalgamation cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add buttermilk, soda and flour sifted with the spices.
Add jam, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Add beaten egg whites; fold in and mix well.
Pour into four 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: scandinavian peach ring
directions: Drain and chop peaches.
In saucepan combine peaches, sugar and cardamon; bring to a boil and reduce to thick.
Add nuts after this is achieved.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix in a saucepan the sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add beets.
Let stand 30 minutes or more. Just before serving, bring to the boiling point.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter or margarine and milk in saucepan. Cook until it forms soft ball in water.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Beat until thick, then drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a large bowl and stir well.
Mix eggs, vanilla and oil with dry ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Cook at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cocoa buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup of the confectioners sugar in deep mixing bowl.
Gradually add remaining confectioners sugar with the milk and vanilla.
Add the cocoa powder until desired flavor and/or color is reached.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Crumble cake in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend milk and cream cheese.
Pour over cake.
Add a layer of Cool Whip.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch on top of stove until it boils.
Add Jell-O.
Continue cooking until it thickens.
Cool.
Add strawberries.
Pour over Cool Whip.
Chill.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread(low cholesterol)
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites or egg substitute with sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and raisins.
By hand, stir in flour mixture just until flour is blended.
Spray 2 (4 x 8-inch) loaf pans with vegetable cooking spray and dust with 2 teaspoons flour.
Divide batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves or 32 (1-slice) servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef, add onion, green pepper and celery; cook until onions are tender.
Drain fat.
Add soup and seasonings.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon, onion and ground beef until done.
Drain butter beans and kidney beans.
Add to all other ingredients.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: red dog soup
directions: Pour soup into a medium, microwave-safe bowl.
Add milk.
Stir. Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Add hot dogs.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir well.
Pour into bowls.
Make strips of American cheese to place on top.
Stir.
Serves 3.

title: wild sage bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Beat egg and cheese until smooth; add melted shortening and yeast.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl, adding flour mixture slowly and beating after each addition until stiff.
Cover dough with cloth and let rise for 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Brush top with butter.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Boil hot dogs after slicing into bite-size pieces.
Drain. Mix jelly and mustard in frying pan.
Heat until melted and add cooked hot dog bites.
Keep hot until ready to serve with party toothpicks.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: Mix green pepper, onion and bacon together.
Then add beans, sugar, liquid smoke and catsup.
Mix well.
Put in a long pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear or shred lettuce and spread over bottom of wide, 4-quart serving dish.
Thinly slice onions and part of tops, scatter over lettuce.
Drain and slice water chestnuts, sprinkle over onions. Add chopped green pepper.
Next, add celery.
Top with English peas.
Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Use enough to cover vegetable layers completely.
Sprinkle with sugar, grated Parmesan cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Top with eggs and bacon bits.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Best if overnight.

title: sweet sour dressing
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
thoroughly
and cook on medium heat until thick.
If too thick, add some water.
Tastes good in potato salad or macaroni salad.

title: tex-mex spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Brown beef and onions; drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce to beef; mix well.
Pour beef mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Cook until mixture makes hard ball in bowl of water.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Then add rest of mixture, a little at a time, and beat.
Add nuts and stir. Drop on wax paper with spoon.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: aileen's mints
directions: Start with 3/4 box of confectioners sugar; add egg white, butter and oil of peppermint.
Add cream.
Start mixing together until it's a batter like dough; keep working with it adding a little cream until dough becomes creamy, working with hands all the time.
Pinch off a little; roll it and cut it like mints. That's all there is to it.
Make sure dough is creamy.
If it is too dry, it won't roll out, it just crumbles.
Be sure not to get too much cream at a time or you'll have to add more and more sugar.
You can use up to two boxes of sugar and add food coloring.

title: spinach and artichokes
directions: Cook spinach just until thawed, then drain.
Soften cream cheese and blend in butter and lemon juice; pour over spinach. Stir in seasonings and artichokes.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and cover with foil.
Punch a few holes in foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix oats, sunflower seeds, wheat germ and sesame seed in a large roasting pan.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix.
Heat oil, honey and water together until combined and add to other mixture.
Add coconut and mix.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours or more, stirring every 30 minutes.
Allow to cool in the oven.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on tortillas to edges.
Sprinkle each with green onions, olives and pimentos.
Roll tortillas tightly like a cigar.
Chill.
Before serving, cut tortillas into 3 pieces.
Use salsa for dipping.

title: rumaki(microwave needed)
directions: Place chicken livers and water chestnuts in a bowl.
Pour on sauce and refrigerate 1 hour. Drain.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use greased loaf pans.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: jelly icing
directions: In double boiler, over boiling water, beat consistently the ingredients until the jelly melts.
Remove from heat; beat until mixture will hold its shape, using electric mixer.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash and hull strawberries. Cover with boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain. Put berries in kettle with 3 cups sugar; stir berries and sugar until all coated.
Turn off heat and let stand 3 minutes.
Add remaining sugar and stir over heat until sugar is dissolved.
Let boil 3 minutes more; remove from heat and let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot sterilized glasses and seal with paraffin.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Line casserole with layer of chile peppers.
Cover with cheese and top with another layer of peppers.
Beat eggs, salt and milk. Pour over cheese and bake 45 minutes at 350° until custard sets.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread dough and let it rise. Spread table with olive oil and stretch dough on it to size of French bread.
Sprinkle dough with oregano.
Lay pepperoni all over and top that with cheese. Fold in thirds and tuck ends.
Sprinkle a little oregano on top. Bake on foil for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Spread marshmallows.
Return to oven and melt.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon together until well blended.
Press all except 3 tablespoons of this into a 9-inch round or square pan.

title: sausage fried rice
directions: In large skillet saute sausage, green onions and garlic in oil until sausage is browned.
Stir in rice and soy sauce.
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Push rice mixture to sides of skillet; pour eggs in center.
When eggs begin to set, break up with fork and stir into rice mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley; serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter.
Press in bottom of pan for crust.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks butter for 10 minutes.
Pour on top of crust.
Layer last 4 ingredients on top of filling.
Top with nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together and roll in 1/2 cup chopped pecans

title: quick brown bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder thoroughly in mixing bowl.
Beat the egg in bottom of pint size bowl.
Add milk, molasses and shortening; mix.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and stir only enough to mix.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch or 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in saucepan to break up any lumps. Add milk gradually, stirring until blended. Add butter, bringing to a boil.
Stir and cook 1/2 minute. Stir in vanilla and cool.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Heat juice to boiling.
Add gelatin, stir until dissolved.
Cool, add cola and fruit.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine to make crust.
Press 2/3 of the crumbs into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 1/3 for topping. Melt 40 large marshmallows in 1 cup milk and cool.
Whip 1 package of Dream Whip and add to the cooled marshmallow mixture.
Spread half of the mixture into crumbs in pan.
Carefully, spoon 2 cans of cherry pie filling on top of that.
Then add last half of the Dream Whip and marshmallow mixture.
Top with remainder of the crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, pineapple with juice, sugar and sour cream.
A mixer, blender or food processor may be used to mix for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Garnish with whipped topping, additional pineapple or maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat well the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend well.
Be sure to flour nuts.
Pour into greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini crabcakes
directions: Mix wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients. Mix.
Shape into cakes.
Semi-freeze on cookie sheet.
Cover with additional bread crumbs before frying.
Yields 8 to 9 cakes.
Freeze unused cakes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cut marshmallows into quarters and set aside.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat; cool.
Cream chocolate mixture, sugar and salt thoroughly in large mixing bowl.
Beat egg into creamed mixture. Add extract.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add parts of flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture, blending well after each addition.
Work nuts into batter.

title: cajun cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together into large bowl.
Add eggs and pineapple and juice.
Mix on low speed until blended.
Pour into large, shallow (13 x 9 x 2-inch), greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Put icing on top of cake while still hot.

title: creamy chicken potato soup
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Save broth.
Put oil in large pot and heat.
Add potatoes and onions.
Cook until onions are half clear (not quite tender).
Add chicken, broth and parsley.
Salt to taste.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Remove from heat.
Add Pet milk until steam.
Do not boil!!!
Serve with French bread and salad.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, sugar and shortening; let cool.
Add cold water.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; add beaten eggs, salt and yeast.
Gradually add 7 cups flour.
Place in greased bowl; cover.
Refrigerate a week.
When ready to use, place dough in greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven.
Dough does not require time to rise but it helps if it sets a while.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together and store.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: pesto bread
directions: Unroll French bread dough.
Spread pesto on surface and roll dough back up.
Score and bake according to manufacturer's directions, but it's best to use pan with shallow sides to prevent dripping in stove.
Serve warm.

title: econny fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake like fruit cake.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients and cook over heat until thick.
Stir regularly.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour in dish.
Spoon in peaches.
Pour some of the juice over mixture.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: out of the world pie
directions: Measure sugar and cornstarch into saucepan; mix well.
Add pineapple with its juice; mix well so no lumps form.
Stir in pie filling and food color.
Use a wooden spoon and stir gently to avoid mashing the cherries.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in dry jello.
Let cool.
When completely cooled, stir in sliced bananas.
Spoon into pie shell.
Cover with whipped topping, garnish with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti con spinaci and pisseli(spaghetti with spinach and peas; low-fat)
directions: Set water to boiling and wash each spinach leaf very carefully, removing all the dirt.
Also wash the pea pods.
Put the spinach and pea pods in a steamer and steam for 10 minutes. Cook the pasta until al dente.
Drain.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Crush crackers and add with paprika, salt, pepper, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Melt butter.
Roll chicken breasts first in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place in foil-lined shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mushroom rice casserole
directions: Put rice (uncooked) in 4-quart covered casserole.
Saute mushrooms and drain any excess water, then add to rice.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in 1/2 stick butter; add to rice and mushrooms.
Add salt and fresh pepper to taste.
Blend together.
Then mix in 2 cans cream of mushroom soup and blend in with rice.
Add 4 cups whole milk and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Then uncover and bake for 10 more minutes.
Stir a few times during baking.
If rice seems dry when done, you can add in 1/2 cup milk after out of oven.
Goes good with steak or chops.

title: kugeli's casserole
directions: First fry bacon.
Saute onion in same pan.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Peel potatoes.
Grate potatoes by hand using fine side of grater.
Drain off.
Add bacon and onion to grated potato.
Add salt, pepper, eggs and hot milk to potato mixture.
Mix together. Place in ovenproof casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until top is nicely browned.
Serve topped with sour cream or applesauce.

title: taco salad
directions: Make a salad using Lettuce, Tomatoes, Cucumbers, Onions and Black Olives.
Crumble Feta Cheese and sprinkle on top.
Add croutons. Use (Cristie's) Greek Salad Dressing.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift a few tablespoons of the flour over nuts and raisins. Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add nut meats and raisins. Sift together flour, soda and spices.
Stir into butter mixture. Last, add the applesauce which has been heated.
Bake cake in a 9-inch tube pan lined with buttered paper, in a moderate 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes for "50"
directions: Brown meat, peppers and onions.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer on low, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Better if made the day before.
Makes 50 servings or enough for 20 hungry teenagers!

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Gradually add flour, alternating with milk.
Beat well.
Add black walnuts.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.
Frost with cream cheese frosting, sprinkled with black walnuts.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut meat across grain in paper thin slices.
Combine soy sauce, broth, sherry, pepper and Accent.
Heat oil in a deep skillet and brown steak in it.
Push to one side of pan and pour 1/2 cup of soy mixture over it.
Add onions, celery, bamboo shoots and mushrooms.
Saute 3 minutes.
Pour rest of soy mixture into pan.
Add the scallions; cook 3 minutes.
Serve over thin noodles.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine the sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan and boil together for
1 minute.
Remove from heat and add butter and peanut butter, stirring, until melted.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on a sheet of waxed paper.
Allow to dry for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: meal in a frypan
directions: Brown beef in shortening in skillet.
Stir in onion, tomatoes, beans and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent scorching.
Serves 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all of the ingredients using a few tablespoons of water just to moisten.
Shape into balls and place 1 to 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: new potato skin
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until done.
Drain, cool and halve potatoes.
Scoop centers from potatoes, reserving pulp for another use.
Salt shells.
Stuff with cheese and top with bacon bits. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.
May be prepared ahead.
May be frozen.
Serves 10.

title: chow - chow
directions: Combine chopped veggies.
Sprinkle on salt and let stand for 4 to 6 hours in cool place.
Drain well.

title: cheesy eggplant parmesan(tender eggplant covered in melted cheese)
directions: Mix flour and salt; place in shallow dish.
Dip eggplant slices in egg and then in flour mixture.
Brown slices until golden in hot shortening; drain well on brown paper.
Place 1 layer of eggplant in glass 8 x 8-inch baking dish; top with half of Parmesan cheese, Italian sauce and Mozzarella.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla custard
directions: In a double boiler, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in 2 cups half and half.
Stir-cook over moderate heat until thickened. Cook 2 minutes more.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs; return this mixture to boiler.
Cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and additional half and half.
Chill and freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cavatina
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sausage in skillet and drain fat. Pour spaghetti sauce and Pizza Quick sauce over sausage and simmer together.
Cook noodles as directed on box; drain water.
Combine noodles and sauce together.
Layer in the following order: Noodles and sauce, cheese, noodles and sauce, cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for about 30 minutes.
If you refrigerate, you may need to bake a little longer.

title: karen's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, both sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, powderized oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Fold in chocolate chips.
Refrigerate overnight (very important). Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients with a spoon and pour into a 9 x 9-inch ungreased pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and peanut butter.
Beat until it starts to thicken. Pour in buttered pan.

title: stuffed turkey breast
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in large skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender; remove from heat.
Stir in poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Add milk and eggs; mix well.
Toss with corn bread and whole wheat crumbs.

title: cheese quiche without crust
directions: Combine ingredients.
Fold into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple butter
directions: Cook cored and sliced apples until very tender.
Put through ricer, then add remaining ingredients. Cook for 30 minutes.
Ladle into sterile jars and seal.
Yields approximately 5.

title: regal chicken on rice
directions: Blend mushroom soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup.
Combine remaining soup mix with rice, mushroom and onion soup mix and pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with paprika. Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except onions and cheese, and pour half of batter in 12-inch iron skillet.
Sprinkle half of cheese and all chopped onion over batter.
Then pour rest of batter over onion and cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 400° until well done, approximately 25 minutes.

title: sweet heart salad
directions: Heat pineapple with sugar; add gelatin which has been softened in cold water.
Stir until melted; add lemon and cherry juices. Cool.
Mash cream cheese and cherries which have been finely cut. Mix with pineapple mixture, adding a small amount at a time. Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend Cool Whip with the pineapple mixture.
Chill.
Serves 10.

title: saute mix vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, bring to boil vegetable oil and butter. Add garlic; stir.
Add carrots, celery, squash, zucchini and green and red bell peppers.
Let cook for 10 minutes, stirring continuously.
Add onions.
Add seasoning to taste.
Let simmer until tender.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Melt margarine, mix with Crisco and sugar, add eggs and beat well.
Sift in dry ingredients while continuing to mix.
Add milk and lemon flavoring.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring to boil sugar and white syrup.
Remove immediately.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Add Special K cereal. Drop by spoonfuls, then form into balls.

title: pumpkin stew
directions: Cut off top of pumpkin to make a lid.
Clean out seeds and pulp.
Bake hollowed out pumpkin shell on oven rack at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Fill with hot beef stew; continue baking an additional hour (stew will pick up some flavor from pumpkin).
Remove from oven; serve, using the pumpkin as your serving dish.
Yummy and decorative on a cold fall night.
tags: your own favorite beef stew recipe

title: brazil nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream well.
Stir in beaten egg and vanilla and beat until fluffy.

Stir together flour and salt and cut into creamed mixture with knives or pastry blender. Stir in nuts; shape into small balls (2/3-inch in diameter); place on baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly on baking sheet and roll in sifted powdered sugar.
Store in loosely covered container.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: creative clay
directions: Stir the cornstarch and soda together.
Mix in the cold water. Stir over medium-low heat until the mixture has the consistency of mashed potatoes.

title: middle east salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use Italian dressing and enjoy.

title: old black joe cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour in prepared pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: swiss chicken scallop
directions: In 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch) arrange beans.
Combine soup, wine, chicken and cheese; pour over beans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with potato sticks.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cream soup substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and store in airtight container.
To make soup, combine 1/3 cup dry mix with 1 1/4 cups cold water in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until warm.
Your favorite ingredient can be added, such as cheese, mushrooms or cooked celery.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: whipping cream cake
directions: Let butter come to room temperature in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir cream of tartar into flour.
Alternate adding flour and cream, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° in a greased and floured tube pan.
